title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, sugar, eggs, salt, 1/2 stick oleo and vanilla.
Spoon into baking dish.
Combine brown sugar, flour, nuts and 1/3 stick oleo.
Spread over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: my mother's recipe for molasses crumb cake
directions: Crumb Part:
Combine dry ingredients except baking soda and work in the shortening to make crumbs.

title: spanish rice
directions: *May add garlic, if desired.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix all together, put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate overnight.
Put bread crumbs on before baking (melt butter and mix with crumbs; put on top).
Sprinkle with paprika.
Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before baking and bake at 350° for one hour. Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: garden pizza appetizer
directions: Spread crescent rolls to cover a cookie sheet, ungreased, pressing seams together.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes; cool.
Blend cream cheese, mayonnaise, dill and minced onion until smooth. Spread on baked, cooled crust.
Mix together raw vegetables and sprinkle over cream cheese mixture.
Top with green onions and shredded carrots.
Lightly press into top.
Chill until served. Cut into squares.

title: snow on the mountain cake
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Mix dry ingredients with egg mixture.
Stir in vanilla, dates and nuts.
Spread in two greased and floured 8-inch pan and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Place rolls in pizza pan to form shape of pizza pan. Brown sausage and crumble sausage over crust. Beat eggs, salt and pepper. Pour over sausage. Put cheese over this. Bake at 350° until crust is brown and eggs are done.

title: ditalini and beans
directions: Cook and drain ditalini.
Meanwhile, heat butter in a large skillet.
Cook onion and green pepper until soft.
Add cooked ditalini and remaining ingredients; heat through.
Makes 4 average servings.

title: raisin oat cookies
directions: In a large bowl, beat with an electric mixer until fluffy, the first 5 ingredients.
Mix next 3 ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in last 3 ingredients.

title: corn chowder
directions: Saut green onions in butter. Combine with remaining ingredients and simmer. Can use a crock-pot to keep it warm.

title: potato casserole
directions: Saute onion with 1 stick of margarine in skillet.
In giant mixing bowl, mix potatoes, sour cream, chicken soup, and cheddar cheese together.
Add onion and butter mixture.
Pour potato mixture into 9 x 13 pan.
Melt other stick of margarine.
Toss crushed cornflakes in butter to coat.
Top potato mixture with cornflake mixture.
Bake at 350 for 45 minutes.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Combine and bake in greased casserole for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: oriental stir-fry vegetables
directions: Clean and prepare vegetables; cut into thin diagonal slices. Heat oil in skillet (or wok).
Add the vegetables and stir until completely oil-coated.
Cover and steam on low heat until just tender, 5 or 10 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: corn casserole (1)
directions: Mix above ingredients together.
(Use the jiffy mix as is, do not use the directions for it.)
Butter a 9 x 13 pan and bake at 350 for 35-45 minutes.

title: everlasting apple muffins
directions: Cream butter; blend in sugar, eggs, nuts, cinnamon, soda, allspice and salt.
Mix well.
Add flour and applesauce; mix well.
Batter will keep 6 weeks in refrigerator and can be used as needed or baked and frozen ahead.
Grease muffin tin and fill half full.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 40 to 50 muffins.

title: tortellini primavera
directions: Cook and stir mushrooms, onion and garlic in margarine in a skillet. Add all remaining ingredients, except tortellini, and mix well. Cook ingredients until all begins to pick up to boiling temperature, stirring occasionally.
Now stir in tortellini and cook until thoroughly heated.
Makes 4 servings.

title: braunsweiger ball
directions: Blend and form into a ball.
Refrigerate overnight, sealed in an airtight container.

title: aunt ann's baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight. Place all the ingredients in bean pot. Pour hot water over all to about 1-inch over beans.
Cover and bake at 225° for 6 hours.
While baking, check for dryness, then add a little water.

title: pig cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream cake mix, butter, vanilla and orange juice; add eggs, 1 at a time.
Beat mixture 4 minutes. Drain oranges and add to batter.
Beat only until blended.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cool and frost with Pig Icing.

title: party meat balls
directions: Mix hamburger, soup mix and bread slices. Make into balls. Bake in oven at 350° until browned. Put meat balls in crock-pot with a mixture of 14 ounces grape jelly and 14 ounces ketchup. Cook in pot 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Grease 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 jelly roll pan.
Melt butter or margarine, peanut butter, marshmallows in sauce pan over medium low heat.
Add peanut butter puffs cereal, mining gently to coat. Press into pan evenly.
Drizzle with chocolate.
Chill slice.

title: corn chowder
directions: Peel and cube potatoes, about 1-inch.
Dice onions.
Barely cover with water.
Cover pot and boil 15 to 20 minutes.
Add creamed corn and whole kernel corn.
Add milk and butter.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.
Do not boil.

title: charlotte's pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta and rinse in cold water; drain well.
In a large bowl, combine all other ingredients and pour pasta in the bowl. Add Italian dressing and toss until well blended.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Put crust or rolls on pizza pan.
Mix ingredients and pour on pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: flank steak
directions: Mix together dry mustard, prepared mustard, salt, onion powder and pepper.
Spread mixture on scored steak.
Grill over hot coals 5 minutes on each side.

title: marinated venison roast
directions: Place roast in a shallow baking dish; set aside.
Saute garlic in oil; add beverage and remaining ingredients, stirring well. Pour over roast.
Cover and marinate 8 hours in refrigerator, turning meat occasionally.
Remove roast from marinade, reserving marinade; place on a large piece of heavy-duty aluminum foil. Bring edges of foil up around roast, leaving top open.
Pour marinade over roast.
Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours or until meat thermometer registers 170°, basting every 45 minutes.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Mix cornmeal and the 2 flours together in pan.
Mix other ingredients in a different bowl.
Dissolve the soda in buttermilk, adding this last to the mixture.
Then add the dry ingredients. Bake in covered tins for 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together; place in greased casserole dish and bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top and bake additional 10 to 15 minutes at 450°.

title: coconut cake
directions: Alternate down the line.
Makes 3 layers.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: tuna fish casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender; drain. Add other ingredients.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 375° or until bubbly. Grated cheese may be added on top for the last 10 minutes.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream together shortening and butter.
Add the remaining ingredients, adding flour last and stirring well to blend.
Roll out on floured paper and cut.
If dough is thin, add more flour. Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Beat margarine or shortening until creamy.
Add sugar, eggs and persimmon pulp.
Add flour, baking soda, salt and spices. Blend.
Add nuts last.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
These cookies stay moist and soft.

title: herbed oven potatoes
directions: In a shallow bowl, combine the first 6 ingredients; add potatoes. Toss to coat. Place in single layer on a greased cookie sheet; drizzle with remaining oil mixture. Bake, uncovered, at 450° for 50 to 55 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Brown chopped meat.
Add all ingredients, except cabbage, beans and macaroni.
Bring to a boil; simmer until vegetables are done. Add cabbage, beans and macaroni.
Cook in slow cooker until vegetables are done.
Serve and eat hearty.

title: hash brown skillet breakfast
directions: Cook bacon in 10-inch skillet until crisp; remove from pan and drain well, reserving drippings in pan.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Heat drippings in skillet.
Add frozen potatoes.
Cook over low heat until underside is crisp and lightly browned. Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper; stir well and pour over potatoes.
Top with cheese and sprinkle with reserved bacon. Cover and cook over low heat 10 minutes.
Cut into wedges to serve.
Yields 6 servings.

title: ham ball
directions: Roll in ball and put in refrigerator.
Chill, then roll in chopped pecans.

title: sands
directions: Cream butter and powdered sugar.
Add self-rising flour.
Add ice water.
Work in chopped pecans.
Roll in small, long shapes and place in refrigerator 2 hours.
Bake at 350° until brown, then remove and roll in powdered sugar.

title: curried pineapple pork chop
directions: Brown chops on both sides and layer in oblong casserole dish. Drain pineapple (reserving liquid).
Top chops with pineapples. Sprinkle curry powder, salt and pepper on chops and pineapple. Measure 1/4 cup reserved liquid and pour over chops.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mud hen bars
directions: Cream the margarine and granulated sugar until well blended. Beat in 1 whole egg and 2 yolks.
Add flour, baking powder and salt, blending well. Spread mixture evenly in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle layers of nuts, chocolate bits and marshmallows over top.
Use enough marshmallows to cover top of entire pan.
In small metal bowl, beat egg whites stiff, adding brown sugar at end of beating. Spread brown sugar egg whites over top of marshmallow layer with spatula. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Allow to cool.
Cut into bars and serve.

title: jessica and jamie macaroni pizza
directions: Cook ground beef in a skillet, drain grease and set aside. Cook macaroni until tender, drain and set aside.
Next prepare pizza dough using instructions on box.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes. Mix ground beef, macaroni and spaghetti sauce together.
Add seasonings if desired.
Pour mixture on pizza crust.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Place in oven for 3 to 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: chicken curry
directions: Add the rest of the ingredients to the onion mixture; blend together, then add chicken pieces and 1 cup water.
Let cook over medium heat until chicken is tender, about 1/2 hour.
Serve with rice.

title: brown sugar bread pudding
directions: Combine soft bread cubes, brown sugar, salt, cinnamon, vanilla, milk, raisins and nuts.
Add slightly beaten eggs.
Pour into a greased 1-quart casserole.
Dot with butter over top.
Bake in a slow oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream. Makes 4 servings.

title: hot dish
directions: Set oven at 350°. Butter pan. Sprinkle onion soup over meat. Brown the meat in oven. Stir a couple times. Add the cream soups and stir into meat a little. Layer potatoes and carrots. Add vegetable soup on top. Bake in oven at 350° for about 2 1/2 hours.

title: hamburger chow mein
directions: Saute hamburger and onion together.
Mix together mushroom soup, chicken soup and warm water.
Cook rice.
Mix all of the above ingredients together, except Chinese noodles.
Bake, covered, 30 minutes in a 300° oven.
Uncover and continue baking for an additional 30 minutes.
Put Chinese noodles on top for last 15 minutes.

title: beef bouillabaise
directions: Brown beef.
Add water and spices.
Cook over low heat about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add zucchini and onions.
Cook until tender. Add sherry.
Cook 5 minutes more.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: quick eggnog
directions: Fill a 2-quart glass jar half full of milk.
Add pudding mix, vanilla and nutmeg.
Shake jar until well-mixed.
Add rest of milk.
Shake again.
Store in refrigerator; if too thick, add more milk.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding mix with Cool Whip; then add other items.
Put in refrigerator for 3 hours before serving.

title: linda's chinese spareribs
directions: Mix all ingredients except ribs in a large pot.
Cut ribs in twos and add to mixture.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat.
Keep basting and moving ribs around so they get coated, but don't stick to bottom of pot.
When mixture thickens (in about 1 hour), remove ribs from mixture and bake in oven for 15 to 20 minutes at 350° or broil each side or barbecue to dry them out.
Cut and serve.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Melt butter and chocolate; add salt, sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil and cook over low heat until thick.
This can be kept in refrigerator for weeks. This is good over bread pudding, plain cake, ice cream or anything.

title: easy italian chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Place chicken in 9 X 13 baking dish. Mix oil, tomato sauce and 1/4 tsp. garlic salt.
Pour over chicken. Place mushrooms, green pepper strips and olives on top.
Cover with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Pour over crust and sprinkle with 1 cup pecans.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until topping is firm.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in 1 cup water until tender.
Drain.
Add butter and
stuffing and soups.
Put in shallow casserole and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: spice of christmas life
directions: Put the brown sugar, cinnamon candies, cloves and cinnamon sticks in a coffee pot basket.
Pour the cranberry juice, pineapple juice and water into the coffeepot.
Percolate the mixture.

title: lemon delights (cookies)
directions: Combine the
lemon cake mix with the Cool Whip and egg. Mix well.
Form
into
small
balls
and roll in confectioners sugar. Bake
on a baking sheet at 350° for about 8 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: patty cake
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine, 1 egg and pecans together.
Pour into baking pan.
Mix 2 eggs, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Spread over top of cake mixture.
Bake in oven at 350° until brown. Cool.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix all the ingredients together, except the blueberries, until just moistened.
Fold in blueberries.
Fill muffin cups about 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields about 1 dozen.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix together onion, celery, peas and carrots, chicken soup and broth; pour over chicken. Melt butter; mix in milk and flour. Pour over chicken mixture. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chicken-almond soup
directions: Saute chopped onion in butter until golden brown.
Stir in stock.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add rice, salt, pepper and turmeric (or saffron).
Stir and simmer 20 minutes more.
Add almonds, chopped egg yolks, parsley and chicken.
Cook for an additional 10 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chicken breasts with artichoke hearts
directions: Coat chicken with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in oil. Remove from pan.
Saute onion in remaining oil.
Stir in wine, broth and spices.
Bring to boil.
Return chicken to pan.
Add artichoke hearts.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until chicken is done.
Serve with rice or egg noodles.

title: still another salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate in container (preferably glass) with covering, overnight. Be careful when using for the first time; it's hot. Keep refrigerated when not in use.

title: pepper steak
directions: Trim fat from beef.
Cut beef into strips (2 x 2 x 1/4-inch). Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add beef; cook, turning frequently, until brown, about 5 minutes.
Stir in water, onion, garlic salt and ginger; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 12 to 15 minutes for round steak, 5 to 8 minutes for sirloin.
Add green pepper strips during last 5 minutes of simmering.
While beef simmers, cook instant rice as directed on package for 4 servings. Blend cornstarch, sugar and soy sauce; stir into beef mixture. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Cut each tomato into eighths and place on beef mixture. Cover; cook over low heat just until tomatoes are heated through, about 3 minutes.
Serve with rice.
Makes 4 servings, 760 calories per serving.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Stir in butter, egg and Parmesan cheese. Shape in buttered pie plate.
Add Ricotta and sauteed sausage meat.
Cover with tomato sauce; top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: finger jello
directions: Mix Knox and Jell-O together. Add boiling water. Stir. Pour into 13 x 9 pan. Chill.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil except for soda and nuts. When a rolling boil is reached, add soda.
Cook to soft boil stage.
Remove from heat and beat until thick.
Add nuts.
Pour into desired pan.

title: bean bread
directions: Mix together dry ingredients; add eggs and milk.
Stir in drained beans.
Pour into greased pan or skillet.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend Crisco, peanut butter, sugar, salt, eggs and vanilla flavor.
Stir in flour and coconut.
Drop on greased pan and press.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 15 minutes.

title: walnut raspberry brownies
directions: Melt chocolate with shortening over warm water; cool slightly. Blend together eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Stir in chocolate mixture, then flour.
Fold in walnuts.
Turn into well-greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 325° for about 40 minutes.
Spoon jam over hot brownies; spread carefully.
Let cool.
Spread Velvet Chocolate Glaze over brownies and top with chocolate dipped walnuts.
Cut into 12 bars.

title: colorful vegetable saute
directions: In skillet, cook garlic in oil.
Add celery, red pepper and oregano; cook until tender-crisp.
Add beans and carrots; heat through.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate pancakes
directions: Mix pancake mix and water; add syrup.
Cook in hot skillet sprayed with Pam.
Turn once.
Remove and butter.
Serve with your favorite syrup.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg together and blend with first mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
This cake freezes very well.
Serves about 16.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients and chill.

title: red velvet cocoa cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs and food coloring; blend well.
In separate bowl, combine flour, cocoa and salt; blend this into first mixture, alternately adding buttermilk, mixing to a creamy mixture.
In a cup, stir soda into vinegar; fold this carefully into batter (do not beat).
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool completely.
Frost with Fluffy Vanilla Frosting.

title: baja guacamole
directions: Bacon-Cheddar Dip:
In a 4 cup bowl,
combine 1/2 of an 8 ounce package cream cheese, softened;
1/2	cup
ounces) shredded Cheddar cheese, and 1/8 teaspoon chili powder.
Add 2 tablespoons bacon pieces.
Transfer to the divided tray of the Get Togethers	Buffet	Set.
Serve
with
assorted
vegetable dippers.
Makes 3/4 cup.

title: stuffed dates
directions: Open each date and spread with peanut butter.
Dip peanut butter side into chopped walnuts.
Roll date in granulated sugar to coat all around.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Crush or roll wafers (very fine), add coconut.
Mix well and set aside.
Work butter with spoon until soft; gradually add sugar, beat until fluffy.
Add eggs (one at a time, beat after each). Beat until light and fluffy, add alternately with crumbs and coconut mixture, mixing well after each addition of milk.
Beat until blended.
Fold in nuts.
Turn onto a well-greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325° or until done.
Allow cake to cool thoroughly before removing from pan.

title: delicious buttermilk salad
directions: Cut up broccoli, cauliflower and green onion.
Mix all ingredients together.
Can make ahead of time.
Will last in refrigerator several weeks.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar with cornstarch and add water.
Cook until clear. Remove from heat and add jello.
Cool mixture.
Place berries in baked crust and pour cooled mixture over berries.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Brown sausage and set aside.
Beat eggs with fork (add 2 tablespoons milk) until mixed well.
Cube cheese (for easier melting).
Add peppers, eggs, jalapenos (optional), onion, cheese and sausage back into skillet.
Over medium heat, cook and fold (frequently).
Remove from heat when eggs are fluffy and completely melted cheese.
With large spoon, place 2 heaping spoonfuls onto one burrito tortilla shell.
Fold shell over egg mixture; fold in each end and roll.
Serves 5.

title: honey-glazed carrots
directions: Combine carrots and water in medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil;
cover,
reduce
heat
and
simmer
8 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain and return to pan.
Add honey and remaining ingredients;
cook	over low heat, stirring gently, until butter and sugar melts.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: goodie cake
directions: Mix jello and water; set until syrupy.
Combine sugar, butter and egg yolks and beat until creamy.
Add pineapple; beat well. Add walnuts and mix well.

title: chicken curry
directions: Cook bacon until crisp and break into small pieces.
Add celery, onion and garlic; cook until clear but not soft.
Blend in flour.
Stir in milk, water, applesauce, ketchup, curry and chicken broth.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Stir in chicken and simmer 15 or 20 minutes.
Add more chicken broth if too thick.
Serve over cooked rice and accompany with raisins, coconut, peanuts or chutney if desired.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place nuts in bottom of pan.
Mix cake according to directions and pour over nuts.
Mix cream cheese, margarine and sugar; spoon over cake mix.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: derby brownies
directions: Cream 1/2 cup butter; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with chocolate syrup, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in pecans and almond extract.

title: potato salad
directions: Dice potatoes into 1-inch cubes; boil until tender.
Drain water off and let cool.
Add mustard, mayonnaise and salt to taste.
Add pickles, onion, boiled eggs and celery.
Chill before serving.

title: noodles a la broccoli
directions: Peel the tough skin from the stems of broccoli.
Cut stems and tops into bite sized pieces.
Boil noodles while steaming broccoli 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain noodles and return to kettle.
Add broccoli and remaining ingredients.
Toss and serve.

title: chip and nut bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; beat in eggs.
Add vanilla and coffee.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix in 1/2 of nuts and chips.
Pour into 12 x 16 x 1/2-inch pan; pat mixture to edges of pan.
Sprinkle remaining nuts and chocolate pieces on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Yields 24 bars.

title: pickled beans
directions: Cook beans in boiling, salted water until tender, using 1 teaspoon coarse-medium salt to each quart of water.
Drain.
Pack hot in sterilized jars.
Combine remaining ingredients; heat to a boil.
Pour over beans.
Seal in hot, sterilized jars.
Makes 8 pints.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Add melted margarine. Press into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 7 minutes; cool. Have cream cheese and whipped topping at room temperature.
Cream them together and mix in 1 cup sugar.
Pour over cooled pretzel crust, making sure mixture goes to all edges; cool.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add strawberries and pineapple; chill until thick.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Place in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: better-than-fried chicken
directions: On waxed paper, combine crushed potato chips and next four ingredients.
Brush chicken with mayonnaise, then coat with chip mixture.

title: crustless coconut pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, biscuit mix, eggs, butter and vanilla in blender.
Cover; blend on low speed until well blended.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Important:
Let stand for 5 minutes, then sprinkle coconut over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Lower heat, if necessary.
Serve warm or cold.

title: cabbage plus
directions: Put enough water in a pan to cover cabbage.
Add spices and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Add cabbage and cook until tender, about 5 minutes.
Drain and add butter.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except chocolate.
Beat with mixer 5 minutes.
Fold in grated chocolate, then chocolate chips.
Pour into greased, floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Sprinkle top with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: fantastique chicken(microwave)
directions: Puncture skin of chicken in a few places.
Place in glass microwave bowl, breast side down.
Do not seal.

title: 5 layer mexican dip
directions: Arrange diced tomatoes, chopped onions and chopped avocados on top of olives.
Top with shredded Cheddar, Monterey Jack cheese and shredded lettuce (if desired).
This may be a dip, but it's a meal in itself.

title: curried chicken and broccoli
directions: Boil chicken approximately 30 minutes, until cooked.
Shred chicken into small strips.
Set aside.
Boil broccoli according to directions on package and rinse and set aside.
In a medium bowl, mix soups and mayonnaise.

Sprinkle curry into mixture to taste. Spread thin layer of soup mixture on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan; then spread broccoli over bottom of pan; then chicken. Spread remaining soup mixture on top of chicken and broccoli.
Top with shredded cheese and sprinkle curry to taste.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until cheese bubbles.

title: macaroni and beef casserole
directions: Brown beef, sausage and onion; drain well.
Add tomato paste, water, oregano and salt; simmer 15 minutes.

title: apple spice custard cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as package directs, stir in apples.
Pour into well-greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until wooden pick inserted near center comes out clean.
Meanwhile, in medium bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk, sour cream and ReaLemon brand.
Remove cake from oven; spread cream mixture over top.
Return to oven; bake 10 minutes longer or until set, sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cool. Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Makes 3 loaves.
Mix sugar, oil, water, pumpkin and eggs.
Add flour, baking powder, soda and cinnamon; mix well.
Add walnuts. Pour into pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and remove bones.
Line a 9 x 13-inch loaf pan with chicken.
Mix soups and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Mix 2 cups of stuffing, according to package directions.
Sprinkle over mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: santa fe-style chicken chili
directions: Heat oil in large heavy pot or Dutch oven over high heat.
Add garlic, peppers and onions; saute for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add chili powder, cumin and cayenne; cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add tomatoes, breaking them up with a spoon, then broth; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium-low; simmer for 15 minutes, or until slightly thickened, stirring occasionally.
Stir in chicken, kidney beans, salsa and corn. Cover; increase heat to high and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium; simmer for 5 minutes, or until chicken is cooked through. Stir in black pepper and salt.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.
Per serving:
289 calories, 28 g protein, 8 g fat, 28 g carbohydrate, 48 mg cholesterol and 972 mg sodium.

title: buttermilk baking powder biscuits
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Mix in margarine until crumbs form.
Add buttermilk.
Roll to 1 1/2-inches thick.
Cut with an old fashioned glass or donut cutter.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet for 12 minutes at 450°.

title: no peek beef casserole(for the crock-pot)
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Stir together well. Cover and cook on low 8 to 12 hours (high 5 to 6 hours). Serve over noodles or rice. This recipe can be doubled.

title: cumin-honey vinaigrette salad
directions: Whisk all ingredients; blend well.
Toss with crisp lettuce, red onion and carrots for a delicious side dish with any Mexican dish.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Mix together powdered sugar, margarine and eggs.
Cube apples. Fold in chopped peanuts, drained pineapple, cubed apples and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate butter icing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix everything together in a greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lupe's super enchiladas
directions: Brown onions and beef in oil and set aside.
Combine water and chili powder and set aside.
Heat 3 tablespoons oil and add flour, stirring until browned.
Slowly add chili powder mixture, stirring until thickened.
Add tomato sauce, salt and pepper and simmer about 5 minutes.
Soften tortillas by dipping in enough hot oil to cover, quickly remove and drain (very hot, use tongs!).
Place some of the meat in each tortilla and top with cheese and roll. Place seam side down in baking dish.
Cover with tomato sauce, any remaining meat, cheese and grated onion.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Crush pretzels on wax paper.
Mix brown sugar, margarine and pretzels.
Bake for 6 minutes at 400°.
Let cool.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown meat and onion; set aside.
Mix cornmeal, salt, soda, milk, corn and peppers together.
Put 1/2 of the meal mixture into casserole dish; sprinkle meat mixture over this, then grated cheese.
Put remainder of meat mixture on this and bake at 350° until done.

title: cheese rolls
directions: Let set to room temperature.
Mix with hands. Shape into rolls and roll in chili powder.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate.

title: banana milkshake(low-fat, lo-cal, low cholesterol)
directions: Put milk in blender.
Add vanilla and frozen banana, a little at a time.
If a thicker shake is desired, add ice.

title: pumpkin pound cake
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer about 2 minutes or until soft and creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed, 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears.
Combine flour and next 6 ingredients.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture alternately with pumpkin mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Mix at lowest speed just until blended after each addition.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 to 30 minutes.

title: rum punch(some warm holiday cheer!)
directions: Combine apple juice and rum in punch bowl.
Slowly pour in ginger ale.
Float ice and fruit.
Warms everyone up and is great after caroling or decorating the tree!

title: lentil soup
directions: In 6-quart pot, cook bacon until partially done.
Add onion, carrots and celery.
Saute, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes or until onion is limp.
Add lentils, water, vinegar, bouillon cubes and mustard.
Bring to boil; cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add franks, ketchup, salt and pepper; simmer 15 minutes. Voila!!!

title: green apple dip
directions: Mix all together and serve with green apples.

title: citrus delight(by crystal light)
directions: Place drink mix in nonmetal bowl.
Add milk, stir to dissolve. Sprinkle gelatin over water in glass measuring cup.
Let stand 2 minutes to soften.
Microwave on High for 40 seconds.
Stir well. Let stand 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Gradually stir into milk mixture.
Let stand 15 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Stir in whipped topping.
Pour into dishes. Refrigerate 2 hours until firm.
Garnish with mandarin oranges. Makes 8 servings.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans.
Pat into bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cook until light brown.
Cool.

title: formosan fried cabbage
directions: Brown bacon and onion together in heavy saucepan or large skillet.
Drain off some of the fat.
Add cabbage and stir-fry over low heat until cabbage is tender.
Add soy sauce.
Serve over rice and pass additional soy sauce.
Serves 4.

title: chicken flautas
directions: Boil chicken; debone chicken and shred.
Add seasonings. Soften tortillas in a microwave, a few at a time.
fill tortillas with chicken; roll up and fasten together with toothpicks, then deep fry.
Can be dipped in picante sauce as a snack or served with Spanish rice and salad.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
May add more cheese, if desired.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Blend cream cheese with milk.
Add chipped beef, green pepper, onion and sour cream.
Blend.
Sprinkle chopped pecans on top. Heat 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
May also be served cold.

title: coconut-spice cake
directions: Combine first three ingredients; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour and next four ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with the flour mixture.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and chopped pecans.
Pour batter into two greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Cool cake layers in pans 10 minutes.
Remove layers from pans and cool on wire racks.
Spread with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: fruit salad
directions: Stir together and chill.

title: chocolate bars
directions: Prepare the dry mix in a big glass container.
Call this your Master Mix.
It will last 6 to 12 months.
All you need to add is the eggs, oil and vanilla.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit.
Dice all fruit, except oranges.
Put in large bowl.
Add oranges, orange juice and marshmallows.
Mix together and serve.
(Apples, grapes, cherries or raisins add a nice touch.)

title: spicy sauce
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in oil until tender (about 4 minutes); stir often.
Add tomato sauce, chili sauce, wine and lemon slice.
Bring to a boil; lower heat, cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; cool to room temperature and remove lemon slices before serving.
Makes about 2 1/4 cups.
Sauce can also be made a day ahead and refrigerated.
Bring to room temperature before serving.

title: apple turnovers
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In mixing bowl, cut the 2/3 cup oleo into flour and salt.
Mix until pea-sized bits are formed.
Stir in cold water.
Form into a ball.
Chill until ready to use.

title: tuna patties
directions: Drain tuna and mix together all ingredients.
Form into patties.
Fry in hot grease about 1 minute on each side.
Pat with paper towel.

title: french apple pie
directions: For top crust mix together, 1/2 c. flour, 1/2 c. brown sugar and 1/4 c. butter, put on top and bake.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, crush bacon, add chopped onion and mix well. Add catsup, brown and white sugars, salt, mustard, vinegar, pork and beans, kidney beans and butter beans. Mix well. Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles, about 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: nettie's green peas
directions: Combine all ingredients in pot.
Cook until onion is tender. This is my Mom's concoction and it's really good.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt margarine in an 8-inch round cake pan. Drain pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup syrup. Arrange pineapple in bottom of cake pan with melted margarine. Cover with brown sugar.
In a bowl, cream together shortening and sugar. Add egg and vanilla. Beat until fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with pineapple syrup.
Spread over pineapple. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Invert on plate. Serve warm.

title: southern poppy seed chicken(serves 4 to 6)
directions: In 1 1/2-quart baking dish, blend soup and sour cream.
Add chicken and mix.
Combine cracker crumbs, oleo and poppy seed. Sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind raw cranberries, oranges and nuts.
Drain pineapple; add 1 cup sugar.
Put jello and remaining sugar in another bowl. Dissolve in a cup of boiling water.
Add cranberry mixture.
Mix until thick.
Put in jars.
It will keep for a long time in the refrigerator.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add chili.
Cube cheese and add to meat.
Stir constantly until cheese is melted.

title: karen's cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth, creamy and well blended.
Line small bowl with Saran Wrap and mold cheese mixture to sides of bowl.
Refrigerate for several hours, unwrap and serve with crackers.

title: impossible pie
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar, flour, milk, vanilla, coconut and melted butter.
Pour into two greased 9-inch pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.
This will make 2 pies without crust.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken breasts in water just to cover.
When cool, cut into bite size pieces and set aside.
Pour bag of chips in chicken broth to soak it up.
Set aside.
Melt margarine and saute onion. Add soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Stir and heat until mixed.
Add chicken and chips, stir until well mixed.
Pour in casserole dish. Top with grated cheese and bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Preheat oven 350°.
Mix 3/4 bag of stuffing, melted butter and one cup of broth.
Put this in a medium size casserole dish. Mix soup, cooked chicken (tear into bite size pieces), sour cream, rest of the broth and the sauteed onions.
Pour over stuffing mixture.
Cover with remaining 1/4 stuffing.
Bake 30-40 minutes.

title: senator russell long sweet potatoes
directions: Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes

title: peach jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and water in pan.
Bring to boil until Jell-O is dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Add pineapple and peaches.
In separate bowl, combine milk and cream cheese.
Beat until smooth. Add to Jell-O mix.
Sprinkle pecans over top.
Place in refrigerator to congeal.

title: cheese cake(heavy)
directions: Cheese should be at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients together.
If lumpy, use electric mixer until creamy.
Use large spring cake pan.
Bake at 500° for 15 minutes, then at 200° for 45 minutes.
Turn oven off and let sit in oven for at least 2 hours undisturbed.
Then refrigerate for at least 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Serve plain or with your favorite topping.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: To 1 cup persimmon pulp, add 1 cup sugar, 4 tablespoons honey and 4 tablespoons orange juice.
Heat and stir until sauce comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and let cool before serving.
May be stored in refrigerator.

title: mediterranean stew
directions: In a 3 1/2-quart electric slow crockery cooker, place potatoes, carrots, onions and stew meat.
In medium bowl, combine tomato sauce, wine, vinegar, brown sugar, salt, cumin, garlic powder and pepper; stir in raisins, stick cinnamon, cloves and bay leaf.
Pour mixture over meat in cooker.
Cover and cook on high heat setting for 5 to 6 hours, or on low for 10 to 12 hours, or until tender.
Remove stick cinnamon, bay leaf and cloves before serving.
Makes 5 or 6 servings.

title: pinon cakes i i
directions: Puree the nuts in a blender or chop and then roll with a rolling pin to a coarse meal.
Mix the pinon meal with the water and salt to form a stiff batter.
Let batter stand at room temperature for about an hour before cooking.
Place oil in a large heavy skillet; heat until a drop of water will sizzle.
Drop pinon batter from a spoon, shaping into 6 cakes about 3 1/2-inches in diameter with a well-greased spatula.
Reduce heat and brown cakes slowly on each side.
Serve hot or cold as a bread.
Makes 6 cakes.

title: quick cinnamon rolls
directions: Grease a bundt pan. Break frozen rolls apart. Put in pan while frozen. Mix dry ingredients and pour over dough. Melt butter and pour over that. Let stand in warm place overnight. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: grama todd's date cake
directions: Cut up dates and pour 1 cup boiling water and 1 teaspoon soda over dates.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Mix together walnuts, eggs, sugar, butter, flour and baking powder.
Add date mixture and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Serve with whipped cream topping.

title: carmen's drink mix
directions: One square (1 ounce) unsweetened chocolate equals 3 tablespoons unsweetened cocoa powder plus one tablespoon shortening or cooking oil.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat and drain. Stir in salsa, corn, dressing and chili powder.

title: homemade chili(chili cook off entry - 1994)
directions: Brown the meat in hot fat; add pepper and onion and fry until brown.
Add tomato sauces, paprika, salt and water.
Cook meat until tender; drain beans and add to meat.
Bring to boil and thicken with flour, if desired.

title: fruit cake
directions: Dredge	cherries,
pineapple and dates with flour.
Add coconut, nuts
and	milk;
mix
well.
Line
loaf pan with wax paper and pack mixture in pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased muffin tins or line tins with paper cups.
Bake at 425° for 17 to 22 minutes. Makes a bunch!
Plan to freeze some for later use.

title: banana boats
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine peanuts, coconut, nutmeg, 1/4 cup powdered sugar and cinnamon. Divide dinner rolls into 4 rectangles. Sprinkle peanut mixture onto each piece of dough.
Dip each banana into lemon juice, then into maple syrup.
Place banana on end piece of dough and roll up ending with seam down.
Pinch edges well to seal. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: homemade banana ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients; add enough homogenized milk to blend well.
Pour into ice cream freezer and add enough milk to bring level to fill line.

title: maple pecan pie
directions: Place rack on lowest position in oven and preheat to 350°.

title: medieval times herb-basted potatoes
directions: Parboil potatoes just until tender.
Melt butter in saucepan. Add the next 5 ingredients; mix well.
Place potatoes on baking sheet.
Generously brush butter mixture over all sides of potato halves.
Season to taste with white and/or lemon pepper.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cranberry-apple cider bread
directions: Grease well and flour 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan. Preheat oven to 325°.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients together until mixed well, dressing should be thick.
Store in tightly covered jar in refrigerator. Stir well before using.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: super easy dip
directions: Pour pick-a-pepper over cream cheese.
Serve with crackers or veggies.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Take flour and mix orange slices, dates, coconut and candied fruit.
Cream butter and sugar together, then add 1 egg at a time. Add remaining ingredients, then add flour mixture gradually. Preheat oven to 275°.
Bake 3 hours in tube pan.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Cream margarine and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add alternately with milk, mixing well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange apple slices in diagonal rows on top.
Combine 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hot wassail
directions: Cook over low heat until red hots melt.
You can use all pineapple or apple juice.

title: cheese chicken
directions: Crush cheese crackers (not too fine).
Dip chicken in butter and roll in crackers.
Put in lightly greased pan.
Push close together.
Pour a little butter and remaining crackers on top. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Can be used with all chicken parts.

title: cinnamon puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Stir sugar and cinnamon in a small bowl, until mixed.
Cut biscuits in half.
Dip tops in melted butter, then in cinnamon-sugar.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheets with the top up.
Use any left over cinnamon-sugar on toast.
Bake about 8 minutes or until golden.
Wrap in aluminum foil; keep warm.

title: cream of broccoli soup(low-fat)
directions: Cook broccoli until tender and set aside.
Combine milk and margarine in a medium saucepan until thoroughly heated, but do not boil.
Stir in potato and onion flakes.
Mash the broccoli well and blend it into milk potato mixture.
(For a smoother consistency, place the milk potato mixture in a blender, add the broccoli, and process for 30 seconds.
Scrape down the sides and process for another 30 seconds.
Return to the saucepan.)
Stir in the broth or bouillon, water and pepper.
Simmer for 10 minutes, stirring frequently to prevent sticking.
Makes four 1 cup servings.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream fat, eggs and sugar.
Make paste of cocoa and part of food coloring.
Add this and rest of coloring to creamed mix. Sift flour and salt and alternate with buttermilk.
Add vinegar. Stir soda and vanilla; add to batter.
Mix well.
Bake in 2 (8-inch) pans for 30 minutes at 350°.
(May use green food coloring.)

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Beat eggs with sugar. Mix all ingredients together in casserole. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients and form into loaf.
Place in shallow 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Combine vinegar, mustard, sugar, water and tomato sauce and pour over meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: calico bean casserole
directions: Drain all beans and save.
Cook chopped bacon; drain.
Fry meat and onion in same pan.
Combine ingredients, except cheese.

title: quick fix casserole
directions: Put enough Tater Tots in bottom of casserole pan to cover bottom of pan and bake as directed on bag.
Brown meat in skillet and drain.
Add both cans of soup (do not add water) and dry onion mix to meat.
Mix well and pour over precooked Tater Tots.
Top with cheese and serve.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Prepare dressing according to package directions to make 8 ounces.
Cook and drain both pastas, allow to cool.
In a large mixing bowl combine all of the ingredients, toss with garlic herb dressing and refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese for more flavor.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and mix together.
Refrigerate.

title: yummy chicken or turkey divan
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put broccoli; layer chicken on top of broccoli.
Mix in a bowl, soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over broccoli and chicken.
Sprinkle cheese over the sauce.
Take bread cubes and mix with margarine.
Sprinkle bread cubes on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Mix well buttermilk, baking soda and sugar, let stand for 5 minutes.
Add Karo and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture forms soft ball in cold water.
Add marshmallows, margarine and vanilla.
Remove from heat and beat well.
Add nuts.
Mix well. Spoon onto well-greased wax paper.

title: barbecued hamburger
directions: Saute onions and green peppers in cooking oil for 3 minutes. Add hamburger and cook until red color disappears.
Drain and add mustard, catsup, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 10 minutes and serve in toasted, buttered buns with a thin slice of onion.
Serves 8.

title: easy raspberry trifle
directions: Bake and cool cake as directed on package for angel food (tube) pan.
Tear cake into about 3/4-inch pieces.

title: ornaments(non-edible recipe)
directions: Mix flour and salt; add water and oil slowly; stir until well blended.
Knead dough until soft.
Roll out and use cookie cutters to cut into shapes.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°, until hard. When cool, paint and decorate ornaments.
You can varnish, too.

title: sweet corn tomalito
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Blend 3 cups corn and 3/4 cup milk in blender until smooth.
Whip butter, masa and sugar together in food processor until light and fluffy (about 2 minutes).
Add all ingredients, including the pureed corn and the remaining 3 cups whole corn kernels and mix well.
Pour the mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil.
Set the pan in a large roasting pan.
Pour enough cool water into the roasting pan to reach 3/4-inch up the outside of the 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until the corn mixture registers 175° on an instant-read thermometer and the corn mixture is set.
Scoop out portions of the pudding and serve hot.

title: lemon squares
directions: Blend together and press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 325°.

title: coconut sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs. Mix flour, soda and salt. Add sour cream, alternately with flour mixture to butter, sugar and eggs. Add flavorings. Bake in well-greased tube pan at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked spinach casserole
directions: Spray a medium casserole dish with Pam. Saute onion, garlic and celery in butter. Do not brown. Stir in frozen spinach. Cook until tender. Remove from heat. Stir in sour cream and add beaten egg and seasonings. Place in casserole. Sprinkle with seasoned bread crumbs, if desired. Bake at 350° until set, about 30 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve the jell-o in hot water. Allow to cool, then add the remaining ingredients. Refrigerate until set firm, then serve.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat. Add Rice Krispies cereal.
Stir until well coated.

title: grape and broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar and pour over broccoli and grapes.
Add bacon and sesame seed just before serving.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in heavy saucepan.
Bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Chill after putting in pan for 2 hours or until hard.

title: green beans and new potatoes
directions: I cook beans until half done, then add the new potatoes and cook until tender.
I then drain the juice off and add milk.
This tastes good and you don't get all that green off the beans! Season with salt.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, peanuts and salt.
Mix well. Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Stir.
Cook 3 more minutes. Add butter and vanilla.
Cook 2 more minutes.
Add soda.
Pour on greased dish.
Let cool for 1 hour.
Act quick each time you stir or it will burn.

title: hot homemade cookies in 15 minutes
directions: Mix both sugars, oats and flour thoroughly in your largest bowl (or cooking pot) with a whisk.
Add cereal, chocolate and vanilla chips and nuts.
Mix with spoon until well blended. Divide mix equally in 6 small freezer bags.
Put 2 to 2 1/2 cups in each bag; zip shut.
They keep indefinitely.
Makes 6 batches.

title: toffee
directions: Sprinkle nuts over greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Mix oleo and sugar in saucepan.
Boil for 5 minutes (very hard ball stage).
Pour over nuts.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top; spread when melted. Cut into squares before set.

title: microwave rice pilaf
directions: Combine butter, onion and celery in a 2-quart glass casserole

title: champagne salad
directions: Cream together softened cream cheese and sugar.
Add fruit and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Freeze. Thaw about 20 minutes prior to serving.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Put bread crumbs in dish and spread the crumbled, cooked sausage over the bread crumbs.
In a large bowl, beat eggs and milk with a fork.
Add salt and mustard; pour over sausage and top with cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika. Cook at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until brown.

title: pumpkin soup(southern soup)
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in a large saucepan.
Add scallions and onion; cook until almost soft, but not brown.
Add pumpkin, chicken stock and salt.
Simmer until pumpkin is soft.
Stir in flour kneaded with 1 tablespoon butter and bring the soup to a boil.
Press the soup through a fine sieve or puree it in a blender.
Correct the seasoning and add light cream and 1 tablespoon butter.
Heat the soup just to the boiling point and serve it garnished with the tiny toasted croutons and whipped cream.

title: peanut butter marbled brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Prepare Peanut Butter Filling.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Combine chicken, soy, vinegar, molasses, ginger and cornstarch in bowl.
Cut squash into 3 x 1/2 x 1/2-inch sticks.
Cut broccoli flowerets from stems.
Pare stems; cut in same pieces as flowerets.
Bring 1 cup water to boiling in Dutch oven.
Add broccoli stems.
Cook, covered, 4 minutes.
Add squash and broccoli flowerets.
Cook, covered, 3 minutes until tender-crisp. Drain vegetables in colander.
Wipe pan with paper toweling.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Combine peas, peppers, onion, pickles, celery, tomato and cucumber.
Add salt, pepper and sugar; mix well.
Pour dressing over vegetables.
Allow to chill and marinate for several hours.

title: texas tortillas
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Spread between tortillas and make them 5 high.
Chill and cut in squares.
Dip in salsa.

title: baked crabmeat salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except buttered crumbs.
Put in large flat casserole and top with the buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 24.
Can be easily divided by 3 for 6 to 8 servings.

title: dream bars
directions: Mix 1/2 cup butter or margarine, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1 cup flour.
Press into ungreased 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over base.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over first mixture.
Use a long cake or casserole dish and bake at 350° until done, about 30 minutes.

title: hearty potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and carrots in water until tender.
Drain liquid into a bowl and set aside.
Put vegetables in another bowl and set aside.
In original pot, saute onion in nonstick spray until soft. Add a little reserved liquid and stir in flour, salt and pepper. Gradually add milk, stirring until thickened.
Gently stir in vegetables.
Add reserved liquid until consistency is as desired. Freezes well.
Very low-fat!

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and salt.
In a saucepan, bring to a boil margarine, oil, water and cocoa.
Pour over the flour-sugar mixture.
Mix and stir well.
Add cinnamon, soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add eggs and buttermilk.
Stir well.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown onion and beef; drain.
In a greased casserole dish, combine beef mixture, seasonings, Veg-All and tomato sauce.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: corn pudding(microwave)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 350° oven about 30 minutes or microwave for 15 minutes, stirring about halfway through cooking time.

title: buckeyes
directions: Combine butter, sugar and peanut butter in medium size bowl. Blend until smooth. Roll into 1-inch balls. Chill.

title: lentil soup
directions: Wash lentils, put in large pot with water 2-inches over the lentils.
When it starts to boil, add ham hocks, onion, celery, parsley flakes, bay leaves, bell pepper, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil, then simmer about 1 hour.
Add tomatoes and cook for 1/2 hour more.
Remove ham hocks, cut the meat off and return it to the lentil mixture.
Serves 8.
Freezes well.

title: macaroni mousse
directions: Combine ingredients in order given, reserving 1/2 cup crumbs and soup.
Top with crumbs.
Heat soup and pour over after baked 40 minutes in pan of hot water in 350° oven.
Serves 6.

title: cranberry fruit salad
directions: In a bowl, drain pineapple, reserving juice.
In saucepan, mix together reserved juice, 1/2 cup water and lemon juice.
Heat to boiling.
Remove from heat and add gelatin, stirring thoroughly. Break up cranberry sauce with a fork and stir into gelatin mixture. Refrigerate until mixture begins to set.
Stir in pineapple and celery; pour into 4 cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: rosemary potatoes
directions: Mix together.
Coat sauce pan with baking spray.
Cook over medium heat 25 - 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan. Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugar and cream cheese and beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 20 to 25 minutes or until done and wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: gourmet chicken salad
directions: Toss.
I use kiwi sliced with oranges to decorate top.

title: cranberry-strawberry salad mold
directions: Drain juice from frozen strawberries and add enough water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Bring to a boil and dissolve jello in it.
Add rest of ingredients and pour into mold. Top with Cool Whip after placing mold on a bed of lettuce.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 9-inch baking dish; put layer of graham cracker crumbs, then coconut, chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool. Cut in squares.

title: pumpkin shell casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash and dry pumpkin (approximately 7-inches in diameter; you can use larger, but it takes longer to cook and you may have trouble removing it from cookie sheet.)
Fill pumpkin with two parts apples, one part raisins and one part pecans.
Add sugar to taste.
Add lemon juice, cinnamon and nutmeg. Mix well.
Return lid to pumpkin.
Place pumpkin on a cookie sheet. Bake until apples are tender.
Begin checking after 40 minutes, but it may take up to 1 hour and 45 minutes longer.
This casserole may be served hot or cold.
Serve from the shell, spooning some pumpkin with each portion.
Top with sour cream if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pickle relish
directions: Chop together first 3 ingredients and cover with salt; set aside for 2 hours. Drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Heat until ready to boil.
Fill hot jars and cap with hot lids.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix everything together. Start in cool oven then set temperature to 350°.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: mushroom-dill chicken rolls
directions: Stir margarine into hot water in bowl until melted.
Add stuffing crumbs and egg.
Stir until moistened.
Spoon stuffing evenly on chicken and roll tightly.
Secure with toothpick.
Place in sprayed baking dish.
Brush with melted margarine and sprinkle with pepper.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until cooked.
Mix soup, water and dill, pour over chicken and cook 10 minutes more.

title: everyday broccoli and cheese chicken
directions: Brown chicken in margarine on both sides (approximately 10 minutes).
Spoon off chicken fat.
Combine soup, milk, black pepper, green and red mango peppers and broccoli.
Pour over chicken and cook covered on low until chicken is tender.
Makes 4 servings.
Can serve with noodles or rice.

title: black olive spread
directions: Blend all together.
Place on plastic wrap; mold to shape. Refrigerate for an hour so can freely be removed from wrap.
Serve with melba toast or non salty cracker of choice.

title: potato or macaroni salad dressing
directions: Mix together vinegar, sugar and oleo in small saucepan.
Add eggs and cook to thicken over medium heat.
Stir with egg whisk while cooking.
Let cool down a little and add Miracle Whip and mustard to desired taste.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Combine,
cover and bake for 5 hours at 250°.

title: fruit compote
directions: Spread pie filling in bottom of casserole.
Layer peaches and pear halves.
Sprinkle brown sugar on top.
Optional: Add bourbon or brandy.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Also good served cold.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter a 4-cup souffle dish or 1-quart casserole.
Melt margarine in small saucepan over low heat. Blend in flour, salt, mustard and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat. Stir in milk; heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil for 7 minutes the white sugar, brown sugar, butter, milk and vinegar.
Have ready in large bowl the peanut butter, Marshmallow Cream and nuts.
Mix until cool.
Spread in large buttered pan.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut partially frozen steak in small pieces, sprinkle with paprika and saute fast.
Saute onions until crystal clear, but do not brown.
Set onion aside.
Add salt and pepper to meat.
Mix meat, onions, mushrooms and tomatoes together and simmer until meat is tender.
When ready to serve, add sour cream.
Serve over rice and noodles.

title: fluffy 2-step cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth. Gently stir in whipped topping. Spoon into crust. Refrigerate 3 hours. Top with pie filling just before serving.

title: italian beef
directions: In crockpot, place water and onions. Add rest of seasonings, bouillon cubes, and peppers to water. Sprinkle roast with salt. Add roast to crock pot, turn to coat. Cook on high 3-4 hrs or on low 5-6 hrs. Serve on hard rolls. A family favorite that makes a lot, but the leftovers freeze well.

title: pickled mushrooms
directions: Add mushrooms (drained) to ingredients.
Marinate for at least 24 hours before eating.

title: artichoke-spinach casserole
directions: Boil spinach, drain and combine with other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.
(Freezes well.)

title: microwave delights "cinnamon apples"
directions: Place apple slices in microwave container.
Combine water, sugar, lemon juice, cinnamon and allspice.
Pour over apples. Cover container with wax paper.
Cook on High 5 to 7 minutes or until apples are tender.
Serve warm.

title: lipton california dip
directions: In small bowl, blend all ingredients.
Chill.
Makes about 2 cups dip.
For a creamier dip, add more sour cream.

title: cereal coconut chews
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, then vanilla.
Add flour, sifted with soda and baking powder.
Add remaining ingredients. Form into balls about the size of walnuts and flatten slightly with a fork that has been dipped in water.
May be decorated with candied cherries.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Combine
cucumbers,
onions and green pepper in a large bowl. Add
sugar,
vinegar,
salt and celery seed.
Mix well. Cover
and refrigerate
for at least 24 hours before serving. Makes about 9 cups.

title: cheesy broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on box until barely tender.
Drain well. Stir soup and sour cream together.
Add broccoli, ham and rice.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Moisten stuffing mix with water and spread over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin custard
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients and cook until thick.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes and 400°
for 30 minutes.
To use as pudding, omit pie shell.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Place finely chopped salt pork into a large saucepan and cook slowly until fat begins to fry out. Add minced onions and saute until yellow. Add juice from clams, diced potatoes and boiling water. Cook about 10 minutes, until potatoes are tender. Add milk, clams, salt and pepper. Bring to a boiling point (do not boil), stirring occasionally. Serve at once. Yields 6 servings.

title: chicken livers madeira
directions: In a large skillet, heat butter, then saute livers until lightly browned.
Stir in wine.
In small bowl, stir broth into cornstarch; stir mixture into skillet.
Cook, stirring, until sauce is thick and smooth.
Add salt and peppers.
Serve over rice, noodles or toast.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon into mini muffin pans (greased well).
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: ground nut frosting
directions: Pour milk over ground nuts and cool.
Cream butter.
Add sugar tablespoon at a time.
Add cooled nut mixture and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla or almond flavoring.
Cut angel food cake in half crosswise.
Spread lower portion with frosting.
Replace top layer and frost remainder of cake.

title: lemon barbecued chicken
directions: Mix lemon rind, salt, dry mustard, oregano and Worcestershire sauce in small bowl.
Gradually stir in lemon juice, then oil and scallions.
Pour over chicken in large bowl.
Marinate in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Remove chicken from marinade and place, skin side down, on grill.
Set 3 to 6-inches from charcoal that has reached light gray stage.
Cook for 45 minutes to 1 hour, turning once.

title: sage cornbread dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir well.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: pizza rounds
directions: Brown beef, onion, salt and pepper.
Add rest of ingredients. Simmer 1/2 hour and cool.
Spread on bread.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and grated Mozzarella cheese.
(Press cheese into sauce.) Freeze on cookie sheet, then put in plastic bag.
Take out of freezer when needed and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: jay jay's meat balls
directions: Mix the first three ingredients together and form into balls. Combine the last three ingredients and pour over the meat balls before baking.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: country crock scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat bottom of a 1 1/2-quart baking dish with 1 tablespoon Shedd's Spread Country Crock.
Cover the bottom with potato slices.
Scatter half the onion on top.
Spoon half the cheese evenly on top of onions.
Dot with remaining Country Crock.
Repeat process.
Salt and pepper.
Pour chicken broth over all.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, oil and sour cream. Pour half of batter in 9 x 13 ungreased pan. Mix brown sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle over cake batter. Pour remaining cake batter over cake mixture. Spread to edge of pan. Bake in 350° oven 35 to 40 minutes. Poke holes all over cake with fork. Pour icing over cake.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Mix soup and rice; set aside.
Place chicken in greased casserole dish.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Do not peek.

title: chocolate-oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, oleo and cocoa in a 2-quart boiler.
Place over medium heat.
Let boil for 3 minutes (rolling boil).
Remove from heat and add the oats, peanut butter, nuts and vanilla. Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Let cool at least 30 minutes.

title: chocolate bread pudding
directions: Scald milk with chocolate. Saute bread slices in butter until light golden brown. Pile them in a buttered baking dish.
Add sugar, salt, beaten eggs and vanilla to the milk.
Mix and pour over bread.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve with cream to pour over or whipped cream.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheesy chicken wings
directions: Mix cheese and spices.
Dip chicken in butter and roll in cheese mixture.
Place on foil lined cookie sheet.
Form lip with foil to drain, if necessary.
Bake about 1 hour at 450°.

title: sandwich cookies
directions: Bring to a boil oleo, sugar and evaporated milk, stirring constantly.
When starts to boil add graham cracker crumbs, coconut and nuts.
Cook until thick.
Line a large cookie sheet with whole graham crackers.
Pour mixture over all crackers and top with whole graham crackers.
Frost.

title: eggless, milkless, butterless chocolate cake(rhonda's 1st prize cake)
directions: Mix all together in large bowl with wire whip.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until knife comes out clean.

title: onions baked in cinders
directions: Wrap the unpeeled onions individually in foil.
Push into the coals of a fire or barbecue, and leave for 30 to 40 minutes.
Or place in a 375° oven for 1 hour.

title: lo-cal lemon cheesecake
directions: Combine gelatin and 1/2 cup sugar in medium saucepan.
Beat egg yolks with 1 cup milk and add to gelatin.
Stir over low heat until gelatin dissolves (about 5 minutes).
Add remaining 1/2 cup milk, lemon juice and peel.
Beat cottage cheese until smooth. Chill, stirring occasionally, until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from spoon.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form. Gradually add remaining 1/4 cup sugar and beat until stiff.
Fold in cheese mixture.
Mix graham cracker crumbs, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Sprinkle on top of cheesecake.
Chill for at least 3 hours.

title: cherry bisquick pie (cobbler)
directions: Mix cherries, Bisquick, first sugar and milk,
spread in baking dish.

title: hot lettuce
directions: Place bacon, onion and lettuce in a bowl.
Place vinegar and water in a medium size saucepan.
Add salt, sugar and egg.
Cook until thickened, stirring often.
Pour this over lettuce mixture. Mix well and cover until lettuce is wilted.
Serve immediately.

title: hot toasted mushroom sandwiches
directions: Saute the mushrooms, onion, salt and pepper in butter until the mushrooms are cooked.
Add flour to thicken.
Lastly, add the cup of thick cream sauce.
Let cool.
Remove the bread crusts. Spread the paste on the thin slices of bread to make closed sandwiches.
Cut into triangles.
Brush tops with melted butter. Toast these on 1 side ahead of time.
Just before serving, toast on the buttered side.
Makes 40 small triangles.

title: dumplings
directions: Boil fryer and debone.
Keep broth.
Heat broth to boiling point and drop dumpling mixture into hot broth.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash and
chopped onions in boiling water 5 minutes; drain.
Combine
soup
and
sour
cream in blender. Add carrots and soup mixture to squash.
Combine stuffing with butter. Spread half of stuffing mix in greased casserole pan. Pour squash over stuffing; sprinkle remaining stuffing on top. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter swirl bars
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining dry ingredients. Sprinkle 1 cup chocolate chips and 1/2 to 1 cup chopped nuts on top.
Place in oven for 5 minutes.
Remove and run knife through to marbleize.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: killer bread
directions: Mix all together.
Spread over French bread.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: fruit salad
directions: Empty undrained fruits into a large
bowl.
Add other fruits. Sprinkle pudding mix over top and mix well.
Coconut and nuts can be added, if desired.

title: easy chicken and dumplings
directions: Place chicken in large pot with water, salt and pepper.
Cook to tender, then debone chicken and chop to small bite-size pieces. Bring broth in pot back to a boil and add frozen dumplings, one at a time.
Lower heat and cook dumplings until done, then add chicken pieces back to the pot.
Simmer for a little longer. Serve with rice or cornbread.

title: hearty hamburger soup
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add carrots, celery, tomatoes and water.
Bring to a boil.
Add rice; simmer 30 minutes.
Add potatoes, herbs and spices and cook 30 minutes.
Add cabbage and cook 5 minutes before serving.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken; drain.
Beat eggs.
Mix flour, salt and pepper. Dip chicken in eggs.
Roll it in flour to batter.
Put in skillet with hot vegetable oil.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Add the cornbread mix and Cheddar cheese together with all other ingredients; mix well.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350° in a well-greased pan.

title: super-duper easy chocolate cake
directions: Make the cake in 2 layers and use a piece of string to slice these layers into 4 thinner layers.
Make the filling by mixing the cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Place the filling between and on top of the 4 layers.
Warm the icing in the microwave until it will slightly pour out of the container.
Put over the top and sides, if you desire.
I keep this in the fridge during warm weather.
You can even put nuts on the top, if desired.

title: walnut-raisin bread
directions: In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, cream butter and sugar; add egg and orange juice.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in flour mixture and pineapple.
Stir in raisins and walnuts.
Pour in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan; bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook garlic powder
with
tomatoes.
Cook
peppers
and onions in oil for 20
minutes to 1/2 hour, until soft.
Strain tomatoes. Mix onions	and peppers, plus all other ingredients together. Cook down to
right
thickness
(maybe
an	hour or longer).
Put in quart or pint jars and seal.

title: banana pudding
directions: In saucepan, mix pudding mix, egg yolks and milk.
Cook over medium heat until it boils, stirring often.
Remove from heat. Layer in baking dish vanilla wafers, banana slices and pudding. Continue layers, ending with pudding.
Top with your choice of graham cracker crumbs, vanilla wafers, Cool Whip or meringue.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix and shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°. Drain on paper towels.

title: raisin tarts
directions: Cream together sugar, oleo or butter and salt. Add beaten egg, vanilla and raisins. Mix well. Spoon into pastry lined tarts or muffin pans. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 12 large tarts.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Pour into 1 gallon freezer.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: larry's orange and avocado salad
directions: Pare and slice orange.
Pare and slice avocado.
Slice and separate into rings the onion.
Use salad greens for basic salad.

title: baked "fried" chicken(low-fat)
directions: In large frypan, place butter and oil; heat to medium temperature until butter melts.
Add chicken and cook, turning, for about 10 minutes, or until brown on all sides.
Remove chicken; place in baking pan or casserole.
In same frypan, saute mushrooms for about 5 minutes, or until tender.
Stir in flour. Add soup, wine and water; simmer, stirring, for about 10 minutes, or until sauce thickens.
Stir in cream, salt, tarragon and pepper; pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 60 minutes.
Mix in artichoke hearts, green onions and parsley.
Bake about 5 more minutes, or until fork can be inserted in chicken with ease.
Makes 4 servings.

title: miniature hamburger cookies
directions: Brush wafers with egg white.
Sprinkle on sesame seed (to resemble hamburger buns).
Ice 12 vanilla wafers with small amount of yellow icing (to resemble mustard).
Ice 12 vanilla wafers with small amount of red icing (to resemble ketchup).
Assemble two wafers with mint in middle with green coconut (to resemble lettuce).
Makes 12 hamburger cookies.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in juices of cherries and pineapple.
Add coke, cherries, pineapple and nuts.
Place in mold and let set up in refrigerator.
Grate froze cream cheese over top of mold to give the appearance of snow.

title: cup-for-cup salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat, pepper and onion.
Drain off fat.
Add taco sauce, Ro-Tel tomatoes, chilies and soup.
Stir and simmer 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir well. Bake 25 minutes in oiled 9 x 13-inch pan at 450°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken breasts.
Break into small pieces. Place into dish.
Mix sour cream and soup together.
Pour over chicken.
Melt butter, add crushed crackers and put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Pack sliced
cucumbers and onions (about 3) in a gallon jug. Pour
mixture
(cold)
over
cucumbers.
Let
stand
in refrigerator for 5	days
and they are ready to eat. Will keep in refrigerator for 6 months.

title: black cake
directions: Bake at 350° until done.

title: peanut butter cookies(diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine butter, peanut butter and sweetener.
Blend well.
Add milk combined with egg and vanilla. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add, blending well. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Flatten with fork dipped into water.
Bake about 10 minutes.
Makes 48 cookies.
Each with 34 calories.

title: chicken scarpariello(prep time: 12 minutes; cooking time: 13 minutes.)
directions: Season chicken with salt, pepper and poultry seasoning. Heat 1 tablespoon of the oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat until it is rippling. Brown the chicken in 2 batches, turning once, 3 minutes per batch. Transfer to a plate. Add remaining oil to skillet; add bell peppers, cherry peppers and garlic. Saut 2 to 3 minutes,

tossing frequently; add wine and bring to a boil. Reduce 1 minute. Pour in broth and bring to a second boil; return chicken to skillet with parsley and reserved vinegar from hot peppers. Cook 1 1/2 to 2 minutes longer, until chicken is cooked through. Makes 4 servings; 294 cal., 9 g. fat.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook rotini.
Dice scallions, pepper and pimentos.
After rotini is cooked, add diced ingredients and dressing.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Cool and ready to serve.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients and add to the mayonnaise.

title: german chocolate filling and topping
directions: In medium saucepan, combine milk, sugar, egg yolks and butter. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients.
Cool until thick enough to hold shape, stirring occasionally.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk, water and pudding mix.
Beat until well blended.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.

title: tomato-broccoli chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken lightly with a little salt and pepper.
Cut chicken into 1/2-inch wide strips.
