In medium skillet, cook chicken and onion in butter or margarine until chicken no longer is pink.
Stir in broccoli, lemon juice, thyme, 3/4 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Cover and simmer 6 minutes.
Add tomatoes and simmer, covered, for 3 to 4 minutes more.
Makes 4 servings.

title: marvelous meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/2 cup soup, beef,
bread crumbs, egg, carrots, onions, salt, pepper and thyme.
Shape firmly into loaf. Place in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
In saucepan, blend remaining soup, water and 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Heat.
Stir occasionally.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: barbecue sauce for hot dogs
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender or food processor until the mixture is smooth. Bring the sauce to a boil in a small saucepan and simmer on low heat for about 10 minutes to blend the flavors together. Serve with hot dogs or as a sauce for cocktail franks. Makes enough sauce for 2 pounds of hot dogs.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Blend in lemon extract and vanilla. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add milk.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut out with cookie cutters.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Decorate or frost creatively.

title: gail's first prize chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, pudding and sugars.
Add eggs and cream eggs for 5 minutes.
Add the flour, soda, salt and vanilla.
Stir in chocolate chips, pecans and cornflakes.
Refrigerate dough for 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Delicious!

title: halupki (stuffed cabbage)
directions: Put cabbage (whole head) in boiling water.
Boil for 10 minutes until leaves begin to separate.
Separate leaves.
Parboil 1 cup of rice (makes 3 cups parboiled).
Mix rice, ground round, onion, eggs, salt and pepper.
Stuff cabbage leaves with mixture and roll up, tucking in the ends.
Place cabbage rolls in large pot, placing one on top of the other.
Mix tomato soup and sauerkraut and pour over all cabbage rolls.
Cook on top of stove on low for 2 hours.

title: 2 salmon logs
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature until it can be mixed easily.
Flake and bone salmon.
Add cream cheese, onion, horseradish, liquid smoke and lemon juice.
Mix very well and refrigerate until mixture is hard.
Place chopped pecans and parsley on a piece of wax paper.
Divide hard mixture in half and shape into log or ball.
Roll the salmon into the pecan mixture and refrigerate.
Can be frozen.
Makes two 11-inch logs.

title: chicken over rice
directions: Spread rice on bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Place chicken over it.
In another pot mix water and bouillon.
Empty cream of chicken into pot.
Blend and pour over chicken pieces.
Sprinkle 1/2 package dry onion soup mix over top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir for 8 to 10 minutes more. Let cool and pour over your favorite ice cream or dessert.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal, buttermilk, salt, flour, soda, eggs, corn and cooking oil together.
Pour half of the mixture into a greased pan.
Pour cheese, onion and peppers in the middle.
Pour other ingredients over. Make like ordinary corn bread (not too thick). Bake 40 to 45 minutes in a 375° to 400° oven.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook meat; spread a layer in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Fry potatoes and put this on top of meat; next sprinkle a layer of cheese on top of potatoes.
Scramble eggs to partially done and put on top of cheese.
Top with layer of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Make the night before and refrigerate, then bake next morning.
Serve with toast or biscuits.

title: cheese sticks(makes 70 - 80 sticks)
directions: In bowl place flour, paprika and salt.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Mix in cheese.
Add water and form into ball.
Press into bottom of loaf pan.
Chill 2 hours.
Remove from pan and slice into 1/4 x 3 to 4-inch strips.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.

title: seafood and rice or pasta salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate. One cup of cooked rice will make 2 cups.

title: delicious fudge
directions: Cook butter, sugar, milk and salt over low heat (never rush this part).
Bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
When mixture boils, keep boiling over low heat for 5 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips and nuts. Stir for a minute, then pour into 8 x 8-inch lined pan.
Cool in fridge for a couple hours until set.
Lift out and cut into squares.

title: pasta fagioli(pasta with beans)
directions: Simmer chopped garlic in oil.
Add vegetables and spices. Simmer.
Add beans and chicken broth.
Simmer, checking occasionally to see if some water needs to be added.
While simmering, cook macaroni.
When macaroni is done, serve with bean sauce.
Add grated cheese.

title: cranberry orange with cherry gelatin
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in cranberry orange sauce and pineapple.
Pour into mold.
Let set.

title: gulf shrimp saute
directions: Peel and clean 8 raw jumbo shrimp per person.
Saute in garlic butter
over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Remove shrimp and turn heat to high.
Add chopped parsley and sherry wine to garlic butter.
Sear
for	30
seconds.
Pour over shrimp and serve with rice or fine noodles (fettucine).

title: potato pork chop casserole
directions: Cover bottom of pan with margarine.
Layer onions, potatoes and pork chops.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°, covered with tinfoil.
Uncover and bake until brown.

title: chocolate peanut butter pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In bowl, combine sugar, brown sugar, margarine, peanut butter, vanilla and egg.
Blend well, then stir in flour.
Press dough evenly over the 12 or 14-inch pizza pan, forming rim along the edge.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Sprinkle with marshmallows and chocolate chips; continue to bake for 5 to 8 minutes or until marshmallows are puffy and lightly browned.
Cool and cut into wedges.

title: diane's gone all afternoon beef stew
directions: Put beef, carrots, onions, potatoes, soup, water, salt, pepper, bay leaf and wine in a lightly greased (I use Pam) 3-quart casserole dish with tight fitting lid.
There is no need to brown meat first.
Mix ingredients together.
Cover tightly.
Bake in a preheated 275° oven for 5 hours.

title: baked rice pudding
directions: Cook rice in boiling water for 15 minutes.
Drain well. Combine remaining ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.
Add rice and mix lightly.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli cheese soup(easy and delicious; serves 8)
directions: Saute onion in butter for 3 minutes.
Add water and bouillon cubes and bring to boil.
Add noodles, salt and pepper and cook for 3 minutes.
Stir in broccoli and garlic powder; cook 4 minutes.
Add milk and cheese slowly.
Stir constantly until cheese melts.

title: fish with tahini sauce
directions: Dredge fish with salt and flour.
Fry in hot oil until brown on both sides.
Serve with Tahini Sauce.
Garnish with parsley and lemon.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger; drain and let cool.
Chop lettuce.
Mash Doritos.
Mix hamburger, lettuce, Doritos, cheese, drained kidney beans and seasoning.
When ready to serve, mix in dressing.

title: cocoa brownies supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch square pan.
Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs; beat until light and fluffy.
Add cocoa; mix thoroughly.
Sift together the flour, salt and baking powder.
Stir in the sifted dry ingredients.
Add 1/2 cup walnuts.
Spread mixture in an 8-inch pan.
Top with remaining walnuts.
Bake for 25 minutes, or until done.
Yields 16 two-inch brownies.

title: german muffins
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, buttermilk and 100% Bran and water mixture.
Add dry ingredients and 40% bran flakes. Makes 4 quarts and will keep up to 2 weeks.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: holiday delight
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: pat's spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic until clear.
Add hamburger meat and brown.
In another pot combine tomato paste and tomato sauce.
Add seasonings and simmer 1/2 hour.
Add ketchup and contents of skillet.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Makes a very thick rich sauce.

title: tex-mex muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray 12 (2 1/2-inch) muffin pans with nonstick spray.
In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, cornmeal, sugar and baking powder. Stir to combine.
Add scrambled sausage and cheese.
Stir thoroughly.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Shake in bag with white sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place biscuits into greased tube pan. Melt brown sugar, margarine and 2 teaspoons of cinnamon; boil for 1 minute.
Pour over cut biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes.
Eat with fingers!

title: popcorn cake
directions: Heat together oil and butter.
Remove from heat and stir in marshmallows until melted.
Add peanuts and M&M's.
Pop corn and add to mixture.
Press all in an angel food cake pan.

title: linda's scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix together and put in casserole dish (9 x 13-inch).
Top with corn flakes (crushed) and 1 stick melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mom-mom's pumpkin pie squares
directions: Preheat oven 350 degrees.
Mix together flour, oats, 1/2 c. brown sugar and 1/2 c. margarine.
Then press into a greased 13 inch x 9 inch baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Mix evaporated milk, eggs, sugar, salt, ginger, vanilla, cloves, and pumpkin. Pour over hot base, return to oven for 20 minutes.
Mix 1/2 c. brown sugar, 2 Tbsp. margarine and nuts until crumbly.
Sprinkle on top of pumpkin.
Return to oven for 30 to 40 minutes until knife comes out clean.
Let cool and cut into squares.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: hot milk cake or lazy daisy
directions: Beat eggs well; gradually add sugar and beat until fluffy. Sift flour, salt and baking powder together; add this to egg mixture and beat thoroughly.
Heat milk and butter to boiling point; add to batter with vanilla. Beat slightly.
Pour into a greased and floured 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
When done, spread with topping immediately.
Place under broiler until brown.
Without topping, this cake is great for strawberry shortcake or is great with frosting.
Double recipe for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into well greased tube or bundt pan.	Bake 40-50 minutes at 370°.

title: ritz chocolate cookies
directions: Make cookies using 2 Ritz crackers, putting peanut butter between crackers.
Then dip cookie in melted chocolate.
Very good.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Trim crusts off bread, cut into 2-inch cubes.
Melt cheese and margarine in double boiler.
Remove from heat and fold in egg whites.
Dip cubes into mixture until well coated.
Place on cookie sheet and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes, until golden brown.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: lime salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with hot water.
Drain juice from pineapple and mix with Jell-O.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: scratch cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add sugar. Mix well.
Add salt, baking powder and vanilla.
Alternate flour and milk.
Mix well.
Makes a layer cake.
Bake at 350°.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: In 9 x 2 1/2-inch spring-form pan with hand, mix crumbs, nuts and butter.
Press mixture onto bottom and up sides of pan to 1 inch from top.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl with mixer on medium speed, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Slowly beat in sugar.
With mixer on low speed, beat in pumpkin, cinnamon, nutmeg, ginger, vanilla, salt, cloves and eggs.
Beat 3 minutes, occasionally scraping bowl with spatula.
Bake 1 hour.
Turn off oven; let cheesecake remain in oven 1 hour longer.
Remove.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Cover and chill at least 6 hours.
Serves 16.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large rectangular casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix in one gallon container.
Fill rest way up with water.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix applesauce, sugar and margarine.
Dissolve soda in 2 tablespoons warm water; add to sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Add 2 cups flour, cinnamon, baking powder and vanilla.
Mix 1 cup flour with pecans and raisins.
Combine both mixtures; pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: porcupines
directions: Stir together in frying pan.
Melt shortening first.
Stir in dates, egg mixture.
Stir until thickens.
Cool a little and add 3 cups Rice Krispies in bowl.
Pour mixture over all.
Add nuts. Grease hands.
Roll into small balls.
Roll in coconut.

title: jello strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello and hot water until dissolved.
Stir in crushed pineapple, strawberries and sliced bananas.
Pour half of jello mixture into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Spread sour cream over firmed jello mixture.
Pour remaining jello on top.
Chill.

title: snowballs or wedding cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Roll by hand into balls about 3/4-inch in diameter.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Roll in confectioners sugar while hot.
Repeat again rolling in sugar when cool.

title: strawberry glace pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
Mash enough berries to measure 1 cup.
Stir together sugar and cornstarch. Gradually stir in water and crushed berries.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils. Boil and stir 1 minute; cool.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Spread on bottom of baked pie shell. Fill shell with remaining berries; pour cooked berry mixture on top. Chill at least 3 hours or until set.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: elvis presley cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in 9 x 13 pan. Punch holes in cake with knife. Boil sugar and pineapple for 1 minute and pour over cake while warm.

title: jello pudding
directions: Mix Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Sprinkle dry Jell-O powder over mixture.
Mix together.
Add well-drained fruit, if desired, but fruit is not necessary.

title: potage megali(french mediterranean leek soup)
directions: Saute the leeks and the onions in oil and butter (or margarine) until soft.
Add the tomatoes.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add the tomato paste and the previously drained juice together with the chicken broth.
Add the orzo.
This dish tends to taste even better the next day.
Good Appetite!

title: curry dip
directions: Mix well.
Perfect dip for all fresh veggies.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, flour, baking cocoa, egg yolks, milk and margarine in double boiler; mix well.
Cook over hot water until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla; stir until well blended.
Pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites in mixer bowl until soft peaks form.
Add remaining 1/2 cup sugar gradually, beating until stiff peaks form.
Spread meringue over filling, sealing to edge.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: dairy potatoes
directions: Mix all in large bowl and transfer to 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 2 cups corn flakes and 1/2 cup of melted butter mixed together.
Bake at 325°
for 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: s'mores
directions: Place 1 graham cracker square on a paper napkin.
Top with chocolate and marshmallow.
Microwave on High, just until marshmallow puffs up, about 20 seconds.
Top with second cracker. Peanut butter or sliced bananas may also be added, if desired. Wait 3 minutes before eating so you don't get burned.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Pour drained potatoes into large casserole dish.
Mix together sour cream, Cheddar cheese and celery soup.
Then pour into potatoes, mixing well.
Crush corn flakes and add butter, which has been melted, mixing gently with a fork.
Sprinkle corn flakes mixture over top of potato mixture with a teaspoon.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin logs(2 logs)
directions: Cover two 18 x 12-inch pans with foil.
Mix together ingredients.
Pour half in one pan and half in other pan. Sprinkle on nuts.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Turn cakes out on dish towels that have powdered sugar sprinkled over them so cakes won't stick to towels.
Roll up cakes and towels. Chill.

title: zucchini date bars
directions: Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Spoon into small ovenproof dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: mexican rice
directions: Process garlic in food processor or until chopped finely (about 10 seconds).
Add the onions and chop coarsely, about 6 pulses; set aside.
Chop the tomatoes, about 5 pulses.
Saute the onion mixture and raw rice in the oil in a large skillet over moderate heat until the onions are translucent and rice colors, about 6 minutes.
Stir in the tomatoes, chili peppers and stock and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered, until fluffy, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Mix flour and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Add peanut butter, milk and egg.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles in medium saucepan.
Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Stir in noodles and all remaining ingredients except cheese.
Mix well.
Pour into ungreased 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese; bake an additional 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: turkey pot pie
directions: Mix all filling ingredients together well and pour into a 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan.

title: pasta primavera
directions: In large saucepan, combine all ingredients except spaghetti/noodles.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes until vegetables are tender, still stirring occasionally.
Add spaghetti/noodles and heat thoroughly, stirring gently.
tags: cream of chicken and broccoli soup

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash and slice tomatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
In bowl beat egg and milk.
In another bowl mix flour and meal.
Dip tomatoes in egg and milk, then in flour and meal.
Fry in hot oil until brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: can can chicken
directions: Cook in skillet and pour over chow mein noodles or French fried onion rings.

title: remarkable fudge
directions: Butter sides of a heavy pan.
Combine sugar, milk and butter. Boil over medium heat to 236°.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips, Marshmallow Creme, vanilla and nuts.
Beat until chips melt.
Pour into a buttered dish.

title: lime salad
directions: Drain pineapple (need enough juice plus water to make 1 cup); heat to boiling.
Dissolve jello and add cream cheese (blender works well), ice cream and pineapple.
Refrigerate.

title: phyllis ladd's broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, until it thaws.
Drain and mix with other ingredients, except onion soup mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Remove and add onion soup mix on top of casserole.
Return to oven for 2 minutes to brown onions.

title: easy mix white bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine 2 1/2 c flour and the yeast. In a saucepan, heat milk, sugar shortening, and salt just till warm (115°-120°) and shortening is almost melted; stir constantly. Add to flour mixture. Beat at low speed of electric mixer, 1/2 minute scraping sides of bowl. Beat 3 minutes at high speed. Stir in as much of the reaming flour as you can mix with a spoon. Turn out onto lightly floured surface. Knead in enough remaining flour to make a moderately stiff dough that is smooth and elastic, 6 to 8 minutes total. Shape into a ball. Place in lightly greased bowl; turn once to greased surface. Cover, let rise in warm place until doubled, about 1 1/4 hours.

title: best ever dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar and salt.
Add 1 cup flour and blend well.
Add Crisco and egg and blend well.
Stir in rest of flour and blend well.
Cover bowl with wet towel and place over pan of hot water until doubled in size (about 2 hours).

title: potato dish
directions: Cook 6 potatoes in water with 1 onion and reserve at least 3/4 cup water when potatoes cooked.
Mash potatoes with 2 egg yolks and cooked onion.
Take 3/4 of mixture and line bottom of casserole dish.
Place cooked vegetables on top of potatoes.
Cook together 3/4 cup potato water, milk, butter and flour to boiling until thickened and pour over vegetables.
Place remaining potatoes over this mixture and sprinkle top with shredded cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rich sweet nut roll
directions: This recipe makes 4 nut rolls.
This batter will keep in the refrigerator for 3 days.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and milk, mixing well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown and season ground beef.
Mix together raw vegetables, tomato juice, water, tomato paste, canned tomatoes and sugar in large stew pan.
Bring to a boil.
Add ground beef and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Serve.

title: fruit with lemon pudding
directions: Put fruit cocktail and pineapple together, including the juice.
Drain mandarin oranges and add.
Add the lemon pudding, dry.
Then add the additional fruits you choose to use.
The lemon pudding keeps the fruits from turning dark.

title: pineapple-nut bread
directions: Early in day or day before serving:
Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
In large bowl, mix well first 7 ingredients.
In small bowl, beat egg, pineapple with its liquid and remaining ingredients; stir egg mixture into flour mixture just until flour is moistened.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake 50 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool bread in pan on wire rack 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: grace's barbecue pies
directions: Brown beef in skillet, stirring to crumble.
Drain.
Add barbecue sauce and onion; stir well.
Set aside.
Separate biscuits and place 1 each in muffin cups, pressing up sides. Spoon meat mixture evenly into biscuit cups.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 400° for 8 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 10 servings.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Tear apart one head of lettuce.
Cut 1 head cauliflower into bite-size pieces.
Cook 1 pound bacon until crisp and crumble. Slice red onion.

title: mango frappe
directions: Freeze fruit for 30 minutes.
In a blender container; combine fruit, milk, sugar, juice and vanilla.
Cover; blend until smooth. With blender running, add ice through lid.
Blend until slushy. Makes 4 serving.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Bake cake in a large loaf pan. Take out of oven.
Punch holes and pour can of Eagle Brand milk and the can of coconut milk over cake.
Cool and put an 8 ounce container of Cool Whip over top of cake.
Cover with frozen coconut.

title: blueberry cream cheese pie
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature until softened. In medium bowl, beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Slowly add condensed milk.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla until well mixed.

title: super spaghetti sauce
directions: Remove sausage from casings and crumble into a 5-quart Dutch oven.
Add beef, onion and garlic.
Cook over medium-high heat, stirring often to break up lumps of meat, until browned, about 15 minutes.
Drain off any fat.
Stir in tomatoes with their liquid, wine, tomato paste, Worcestershire sauce, salt, sugar, parsley, basil, fennel seed and pepper.
Heat to boiling, stirring often. Reduce heat to low and simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes, stirring occasionally to prevent scorching.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix together oleo, eggs, cottage cheese and broccoli.
Add cornbread mix.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Stir together first 4 ingredients.
Melt butter in cake pan. Pour milk, sugar, flour and baking powder in pan (do not stir). Pour peaches over.
Do not stir peaches in batter.
Bake at 350° until it turns brown.
Serves 6.

title: turkey lasagna
directions: Prepare the cornbread according to instructions.
Pour this into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan (I used a light no stick spray).
Meanwhile, be browning your hamburger mixed with the onion and bell pepper.
Now mix in the rest of your condiments and pour this into the cornbread mix and pop the whole thing into the oven and cook according to the instructions on the prepared cornbread mix.
This is really good.
I took some to where I work and now it is called "Shirley's Quick Casserole".
Enjoy!

title: cran-raspberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce and stir together.
Add undrained pineapple and chopped nuts. Place in refrigerator until set.
Combine cream cheese and sour cream.
Spread on top of jello when it is set.
Extra good with ham or turkey.

title: sugar free spice cake
directions: Cover raisins with 2 cups water and cook down to soften 10 minutes.
Drain.
Add all to flour mixture.
Mix and bake in a 9 x 9-inch baking pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: round steak and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cube meat into bite-size squares. Spray frying pan with Pam and brown meat.
Drain.
Add vinegar; stir on medium heat until well blended.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: raisin pudding
directions: Sift flour and salt in bowl. Work in eggs, one at a time. Beat in sugar.
Gradually stir in milk, cream and vanilla.
Batter will be very thin.
Spread raisins on bottom of a buttered 11 x 18-inch baking pan.
Pour the batter into pan slowly. Bake in preheated 450° oven for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 275° and bake 1 hour longer or until pudding is set and browned.
Cool 20 minutes, then chill and cut in squares.

title: bohemian kolache
directions: Cream butter, sugar, cream cheese and egg yolks together.
Add flour, baking powder and salt; blend well.
Add vanilla.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Roll dough to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut in 3 1/2-inch squares.
In center of each square, place 1 rounded teaspoonful prune or apricot mixture.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Fold over opposite corners and pinch together.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 12 minutes.
Watch closely as Kolache burns easily.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: turkey shepherd's pie
directions: In microwave bowl, stir milk and flour until well blended. Stir in soup and seasoning.
Cover with wax paper. Microwave 7 to 8 minutes. Stir every 2 minutes until it boils and thickens.

title: chicken and corn stew
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove from heat and debone, saving stock.
Bring stock to a boil again and add chicken, corn on cobb and creamed corn.
Cook just until tender, being careful not to let corn stick to pot.
Remove from heat and add box of crackers or serve stew in soup bowls with crackers separate.

title: family favorite coffee cake
directions: Mix all together and bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Spread butter on top and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.

title: old fashioned chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cornmeal; stir in butter, eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix well; pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 325°; bake for 30 minutes longer.
Cover pie with foil, if necessary, to prevent burning.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together the peanut butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Spoon mixture into the pie crusts and refrigerate until chilled.
Set out to thaw for 10 minutes before serving.
Add extra toppings to decorate, if desired.

title: out of this world chocolate cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each.
Add buttermilk, flour, soda and vanilla.
Fold in dates and nuts.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with buttermilk glaze.
Return cake to oven for additional 10 minutes.
Cool and frost with chocolate frosting.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown onions in butter.
Add vinegar, brown sugar, lemon juice, catsup, parsley, prepared mustard, water, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Simmer for a few minutes.
This can be used with ribs or venison.
Pour over the meat and roast slowly, adding more barbecue sauce as the meat cooks.

title: april's salad
directions: Make shells and cheese according to directions on box and add remaining ingredients.
Mix, heat and serve.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes and onions in a small amount of water until slightly tender. Do not overcook. Drain. Add remaining ingredients. Simmer over very low heat, stirring often, until cheese melts and soup is heated thoroughly.

title: lumpia
directions: Mix and brown together ground pork and ground round.
Add onion to meat mixture and saute.
Add shrimp and cook for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add eggs.
Cool mixture, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Wrap in lumpia wrappers.
Put about 1 heaping tablespoonful on a wrapper.
(Mixture must be cool before wrapping, or wrapper will fall apart.)
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in an airtight container. Use 2 teaspoons per cup of very hot water.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Mix the liquids together and add dry ingredients.
Grease large cookie sheet.
Line with wax paper and spray with Pam.
Put batter on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Sift 1 cup powdered sugar onto a linen or cotton towel. When cake is done, put cake hot onto towel and roll it up until cool.
Unroll and spread icing on the cake and roll it back.
Not too tight.

title: pizza rounds
directions: Cook meat; drain well.
Add other ingredients and spread on pieces of one loaf party round rye bread.
Makes large recipe of 35 to 40 slices and freezes well to be used as needed.
The party rye bread is found in the dairy case at the supermarket.
Regular rye bread could probably be used.

title: bread pudding
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Butter 6 slices of bread.
Add cinnamon and nutmeg on top.
Add the ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding apples and nuts last. Bake in a 13 x 2 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cutout cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll on powdered sugar and cut into shapes. Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° until done.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix together sour cream, cream cheese and seasonings.
Blend in mayo and milk.
Add crab meat (make sure all shells are removed).
Pour in pan or flat casserole dish. Sprinkle paprika on top as well as grated cheese, grated cheese first.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons warm water.
Add yeast mixture to buttermilk.
Mix yeast-milk mixture with flour mixture.
Put in an airtight container and chill for 20 minutes.
Roll out dough and cut into biscuits.
Place on a baking sheet (greased) and allow to sit in a warm place for 10 minutes.
Bake at 400° until browned.

title: champagne salad
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Add pineapple, strawberries, bananas and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and freeze.
Thaw about 15 minutes before serving.

title: cream of chicken with cheese soup
directions: Saute vegetables in butter for about 10 minutes. Add chicken stock and simmer until vegetables are tender, about 15 minutes. Add cream and heat to simmering. Add cheese and chicken, stirring to melt cheese. Season to taste.
Heat through and serve.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and cook in tube pan for one hour at 300°.

title: "miss" linda's chocolate pie
directions: *When doubling the recipe, use only 5 eggs.

title: hidden valley sausage stars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blot sausage dry and combine with remaining ingredients.
Lightly grease muffin tins and press one wrapper into each.
Bake 5 minutes or until golden.
Remove from tins and put on cookie sheet.
Add filling and bake 5 more minutes. Makes 4 or 5 dozen.

title: chicken broccoli oriental
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in hot oil, cook chicken, 1/2 at a time until browned.
Add onion and peppers. Cook 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Mix muffin mix as directed.
Add the cream-style corn.
Brown meat; drain.
Add taco seasoning; simmer for 10 minutes.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 1/2 mix in pan; put meat on top.
Add cheese slices; pour remaining mix on top.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan with cooking spray (Pam).
Mix flour, salt and pepper into paper bag.
Coat potatoes with mixture.
Melt Velveeta and milk together.
Cook until smooth.
Add green pepper, onion and pimentos, then pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until tender.

title: eggplant dressing
directions: Peel and quarter eggplants.
Boil in salted water until very tender (15 to 20 minutes).
Mash with fork and set aside. Saute onion,
celery
and parsley flakes in oil until tender. Set aside.
Brown
ground
round and add eggplant and sauteed vegetables.
Add
wet
bread
slices
and 1/2 cup cooked rice. Add beaten
egg,
salt
and
pepper.
Stir and cook for 2 to 5 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground
beef,
drain
and
cool.	Add to shredded lettuce and drained beans.	Add tomatoes and onions 30 minutes before serving.
Grate
cheese
on	top and add crushed bag of taco chips.
Toss, then add the dressing.

title: enchiladas
directions: Layer in greased pan 3 tortillas, then beans, hamburger meat, onions. Top with cheese, then 6 more tortillas. Spread can cream of mushroom soup over this and add can of Ro-Tel tomatoes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except bacon; put in loaf pan. Top with catsup and 2 or 3 slices of bacon, uncooked.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Drain grease.
Let stand about 5 minutes before serving.

title: crock pot mac-n-cheese
directions: Spray crock pot with non stick spray.
Mix milks, eggs, cheese, salt and pepper together.
Pour into crock pot.
Add elbow macaroni and stir.
Cover.
Cook on low for 3 1/2 hours.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs for 3 minutes.
Add dry ingredients, nuts and bananas.
Mix for 1 minute.
Pour into 2 small loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry cheesecake
directions: Prepare crust for 9-inch nonstick spring-form pan.

title: microwave fiesta lasagne
directions: In a large bowl, combine chicken, salsa and cilantro.
Spread 1/3 of this mixture on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Arrange half of lasagne on top of sauce.

title: chicken broccoli supper
directions: In a large bowl, combine the chicken, broccoli, macaroni and cheese. Whisk the soup, broth, garlic powder and pepper; stir into chicken mixture. Transfer to a greased 1 1/2 qt. baking dish. Bake, uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry delight
directions: In blender add orange juice, strawberries and brown sugar.
If blender crushes ice, add 4 to 5 cubes of ice.
Blend until ice is like snow cone ice.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers, slice celery, green pepper and onion. Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons plain (not iodized) salt and let stand for 2 hours.
Drain.

title: a friend's bread
directions: Mix and let stand awhile. Spread with soft margarine.
Spread mixture and bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Stir. Ready to serve.

title: powdered sugar frosting
directions: Combine powdered sugar in a large bowl with margarine and milk. Beat at medium speed 1 to 2 minutes, until creamy.

title: baked lemon cake pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 1-quart casserole.
In small bowl, with mixer on high, beat egg whites with salt until soft peaks form.
Beating at high speed, gradually sprinkle in 1/2 cup sugar, beating until sugar is completely dissolved.

(Whites should stand in stiff peaks; do not scrape sides of bowl during beating.) In another small bowl, beat egg yolks with 1/4 cup sugar; add remaining ingredients, except whipped cream, and beat until well mixed.
With wire whisk, gently fold egg yolk mixture into egg whites just until mixed.
Pour batter into casserole.
Set casserole in shallow pan; place on oven rack.
Fill pan halfway up sides of casserole with boiling water.
Bake 55 to 65 minutes until top is golden and firm.
Cool on wire rack.
Serve slightly warm or cold, as is or topped with whipped cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: creamy-sure fudge
directions: Combine sugar, undiluted milk, butter, Marshmallow Creme and salt in 2-quart saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture has boiled for exactly 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips and vanilla and stir until chocolate is melted.

title: grandma's pecan fingers
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flavoring, pecans, salt and flour.
Roll into balls and shape like fingers (not too big.) Bake 25 minutes at 325°.
Roll in powdered sugar when lukewarm.

title: mushroom quiche
directions: Mix soup, eggs, milk and spices.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into baked pie shell.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: macaroni 'n' cheese
directions: Mix milk and eggs together in a medium bowl.
Add cheese, butter and cooked macaroni.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat sugar and butter together, then beat eggs.
Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add ice cream to the Jell-O until all is melted.
Break angel food cake into small pieces and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place drained strawberries evenly over cake, then pour Jell-O and ice cream mixture over cake.
Place in refrigerator.

title: cool cookie crumble
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add ice cream by spoonfuls. Stir until ice cream is melted.
Fold in crumbled cookies.
Pour into individual dessert glasses or serving bowl.
Chill until set, about 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.
Garnish if you're counting calories.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Trim off the fat and brown pork chops lightly in a hot skillet.
Mix soup and milk; set aside.
In a casserole dish, layer the ingredients, starting with the potatoes, then the onion, then meat and last the soup.
If more than 4 pork chops are used, it is a good idea to use only half of the ingredients and make two complete sets of layers in the dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until meat is tender.

title: crock-pot pork chops
directions: Mix the first four ingredients.
Coat pork chops with flour mixture and fry in skillet until brown.
Place in crock-pot.
Pour chicken and rice soup over chops and cook on low for 8 hours or on high for 4 hours.

title: burger heaven casserole
directions: In large skillet, brown meat, celery and onion mixture and mushrooms. In slow cooker sprayed with butter flavored spray, combine meat mixture, potatoes, carrots, peas and corn. Stir in tomato soup, water, parsley flakes and salt and pepper to taste. Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook ground beef, bacon, onion and seasonings until onions are tender.
Drain off the liquid.
Put cooked meat mix into large, greased casserole.
Add beans, then stir in other ingredients. Bake at 375°, covered, for 45 minutes.

title: morning muffins
directions: Boil water and add bran cereal.
Let set while mixing sugar and oil together.
Stir in eggs and add buttermilk and oatmeal. Add flour, soda and salt; mix thoroughly.
Now, add the water and cereal mixture that has been sitting.
Bake in muffin tins at 400° for 14 minutes.
Store remaining recipe in sealed container in refrigerator and use as desired.

title: lavender and old lace
directions: Combine water, cinnamon stick and cloves in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Remove and discard cinnamon and cloves.
Add grape juice and lime; stir.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and refrigerate for several hours.

title: healthy salad dressing
directions: *Such as thyme, dill, parsley, garlic, etc.

title: winter stew
directions: Brown ground beef and onion, drain well.
In large broiler add all remaining ingredients and ground beef.	Bring to boil; cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Great on cold winter nights. 6-8 servings.

title: sausage-cornbread casserole bake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 10 1/2-inch skillet.
Brown sausage and onion.
Drain well. Combine eggs, cornmeal, corn, milk and oil.
Pour half of cornmeal mixture into skillet and then sprinkle with sausage mixture and cheese.
Pour remaining batter over top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes before serving.
If using plain cornmeal, add 2 1/4 teaspoon baking powder and 3/4 teaspoon of salt.

title: grapefruit spritzer
directions: Pour concentrated grapefruit juice into a pitcher and add a chilled club slowly; mix well and 4 service.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together 4 or 5 times.
Set aside. Cream Crisco and sugar; add eggs one at a time and beat well.
Add flavoring, then add flour that has been sifted together with dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.
Baking time may vary with each oven.

title: carrots concerto
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter or margarine.
Stir in brown sugar, honey, orange peel, salt and pepper.
Add carrots and cook uncovered over medium heat for 8 to 10 minutes or until carrots are just tender-crisp.
Stir mixture occasionally.
Makes 4 servings.

title: meat loaf italiano
directions: In a bowl, mix thoroughly the tomato soup and spices. Take out 1/2 cup soup mixture and set the rest aside. Combine 1/2 cup soup with beef, sausage, crumbs, cheese, onion, egg and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Shape firmly into an 8 x 4-inch loaf in a baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until done. Reserve 2 tablespoons drippings.
In saucepan, heat remaining soup, water and reserved drippings to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Spoon over meat loaf.
Makes 8 servings.

title: aunt dora's coffee cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, oil, pudding mix and water.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Mix together nuts, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour 1/2 of batter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 of nut mixture on top of batter.
Add remaining batter and sprinkle remaining nut mixture on top.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple supreme
directions: Crust:
Cream the margarine with 6 tablespoons of sugar; add pretzels.
Mix.
Put into bottom of 10 x 18 1/2-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: italian sausage soup
directions: Simmer chicken in water for 2 hours.
Remove chicken bones. Strain broth and set aside.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat egg whites and vanilla until soft peaks form (tips curl).
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff peaks form (tips stand straight).
Fold in coconut.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Cook the sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper; bring to a boil.
Cool; mix with vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: lazy cobbler
directions: Combine margarine, flour, sugar and milk in an 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Top with fruit filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken-cheese rolls
directions: Place split breasts between waxed paper. Pound to 1/2-inch thick.
Spread each with 3 tablespoons cheese. Dot with 1/2 teaspoon butter. Fold ends over filling (some will ooze out during baking).
Wrap 1 slice of bacon around each roll. Place, seam side down, in a shallow baking pan.
Bake on top rack in a 400° oven for 40 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Place top shell on and crimp edges.
Cut 4 slits in top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: stars and stripes dessert
directions: Line bottom of 12 x 8-inch baking dish with 8 slices of pound cake.
Top with 1 cup each strawberry slices and blueberries, then the Cool Whip whipped topping.
Design stars and stripes with 3 cups strawberry halves and 1/3 cup blueberries.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Makes 15 servings.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Combine sugar and butter.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Stir in extracts.

title: peanut butter delight
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions, using 2 1/2 cups milk.
When thick, fold in pineapple.
In a separate bowl, blend peanut butter, graham cracker crumbs and sugar.
Butter an 8-inch square pan.
Put half of pudding mixture into pan, top with half of crumb mixture and repeat.
Chill.
Add whipped topping before serving.

title: sugar-free pineapple dessert
directions: Line
bottom of 8-inch square pan with graham crackers. Drain pineapple and spread over graham crackers.
Mix pudding according to
direction on box and pour over pineapple.
Last, spread half of Cool Whip on top and garnish as desired.

title: rich cocoa waffles
directions: Combine flour,	sugar,	cocoa,	baking powder, soda and salt in mixing bowl.
Add eggs and buttermilk; beat just until blended. Gradually	add
melted butter, beating until smooth. Add vanilla. Bake
in
waffle
iron.
Makes
about
10	to 12 (4-inch) waffles.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: For beef, pork or chicken, cooked on grill.

title: chicken pie
directions: Bring chicken, soup and broth to boil.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine batter ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake for 30 minutes at 425° or until golden brown.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Mix all but soup and water.
Form into balls and place in baking dish.
Pour soup and water over this.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: cold nacho dip
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Serve with corn chips or vegetables.
Makes 2 cups.

title: quick dessert
directions: Mix together the ingredients and chill.

title: cranberry-orange salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in cranberry sauce, cinnamon and cloves.
Chill until partially set.
Add orange sections.
Chill until set.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain.
Add soup and milk.
Season with butter.
Sprinkle onion rings on top.
Bake at 375° until onion rings are brown.

title: pumpkin fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: quick dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: spicy vegetable beef soup(low sodium recipe)
directions: Combine beef and garlic in a Dutch oven; cook over medium heat until browned, stirring to crumble meat.
Drain meat in a colander and pat dry with a paper towel.
Wipe pan drippings with a paper towel.
Return meat to pan; add tomato juice, water and next 9 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in mixed vegetables.
Cover and cook mixture for 25 minutes.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Mix crumbs, sugar, gelatin and butter (reserve 2 tablespoons for topping).
Press in a 9-inch pie pan. Chill about 15 minutes. Fill with pie mixture or instant pudding.

title: apple cider
directions: Mix
first
ingredients and pour in percolator.
Put cinnamon and cloves in filter and perk.

title: bean chalupa
directions: Rinse pinto beans.
Place in a large pot.
Add pork roast and other ingredients.
Pour enough water to cover roast.
Cover pot and simmer for at least 5 hours or until meat shreds.
Stir to thicken.
Serve a spoonful of mixture on taco shells or soft flour shells using other condiments such as lettuce, tomatoes, cheese or sour cream.
May also be served over corn chips.

title: baked beans
directions: In mixing bowl, mix together the beans, onion, pepper, sugars, mustard and ketchup.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour mixture into casserole dish and put bacon on top of mixture.
Put in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil noodles, drain and put back in pan with half and half.
Brown meat, stir in sauce, add garlic and oregano.
Butter 2-quart casserole.
Layer half the meat, half the noodles, half the Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat.
Bake for 20 minutes, covered.
Uncover, add Parmesan cheese and bake 10 minutes more.
Serve with salad and garlic bread.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Beat together margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Stir in the graham cracker crumbs, baking powder, milk and chopped nuts. Pour into a 13 x 9-inch greased and floured baking pan. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: fruit pan walnut cake
directions: Spread pie filling in bottom of pan.
Combine flour, sugar and salt; sprinkle over pie filling.
In bowl, combine eggs, vanilla, oil and 1/2 cup walnuts; mix well.
Pour on ingredients in pan; stir until blended.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Prick warm cake with fork.
Pour topping over warm cake.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup walnuts.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cornstarch together in bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in milk, vanilla and nutmeg, mixing well.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 325°.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: mexican tamale soup
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper. To this, add beef broth, tomatoes, corn, beans and seasonings. Simmer 1/2 hour; just before serving, put in cornstarch. Also, just before serving, cut tamales in 1-inch pieces. Heat and serve.

title: spiced pineapple pork roast
directions: Place roast on rack in shallow roasting pan.
Insert meat thermometer into thickest part of roast, not touching bone. Roast uncovered, at 350° for 2 1/2 or 3 hours or until temperature of 190°.
Combine preserves, honey, vinegar, mustard, salt, cinnamon and cloves in small pan.
Cook stirring constantly over low heat until preserves melt.
In last 20 minutes of cooking, garnish roast with pineapple rings and brush with glaze, twice. Serve remaining glaze warm with roast.

title: holiday delight punch
directions: Pour ingredients over ice cubes in punch bowl.
Blend.
Fresh fruit slices of orange or lemon may be floated on top of punch. Yields 35 servings.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream together butter and peanut butter.
Add brown and white sugars.
Add eggs, vanilla, salt and baking soda.
Mix in chocolate chips and M&M's.
Add oatmeal.
Use ice cream scoop and place on greased cookie sheet, six to a cookie sheet.
Press down. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: birthday cake icing
directions: Add shortening to bowl and beat it. Add powdered sugar, then add water.
Never beat more than 5 minutes.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together pumpkin, sugar, oil and egg.
Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt; add to pumpkin mixture together with dissolved milk and soda.
Mix well.
Add chocolate pieces, nuts and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoons on lightly greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bacon, in large ovenproof container.
Lay bacon strips on top and cook approximately 30 minutes at 350°.

title: faux heath bars
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with separated saltines. Melt 1 stick of oleo.
Add 1/2 cup sugar.
Stir two minutes and spread over saltines.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.

title: apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 400 degrees.
Use 9 inch pie pan.
In large bowl, combine all filling ingredients;
toss lightly.
Spoon apple mixture into pie crust.
Top with second crust and flute;
cut slits in several places.
Bake at 400 degrees for 40 to 45 minutes or until apples are tender and crust is golden brown.

title: olive cheese puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
For dough, blend cheese with butter, stir in flour, salt and paprika.
Mix well.
Wrap 1 tsp dough around each olive, covering completely.
Bake for 12-15 minutes until lightly browned.

title: chicken fried round steak
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces.
Pound steak thoroughly.
Mix eggs and milk.
Dip meat into egg mixture, then into cracker crumbs.
Brown slowly on both sides in hot shortening.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Cover tightly; cook over very low heat 45 to 60 minutes or until tender.
Serve with South Gravy over steaks.
Makes 6 servings.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook sliced, unpeeled zucchini and onions in boiling water 5 minutes. Drain. Combine soup, sour cream and carrots. Fold in zucchini and onions. Combine dry stuffing mix with oleo. Spread 1/2 in casserole and spoon vegetable mixture on top. Sprinkle remaining stuffing on top. Bake until brown at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat together for 1 minute the first 4 ingredients.
Add all other ingredients and beat for 1 minute or until well blended. Bake in 3 (8-inch) pans for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Frost with the following frosting.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into uncooked pie shell. Bake at 350 degrees about 1 hour.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except barbecue Fritos.
Just before serving, mix in bag of barbecue Fritos.

title: frankfurter and sauerkraut sauterne
directions: Melt butter in a large frying pan.
Add onion and apple. Saute slowly until onion is yellow.
Add sauerkraut, 1 cup of wine, water, brown sugar, salt and pepper.
Mix well with a fork. Cover and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Arrange frankfurters on kraut and add remaining 1/2 cup wine.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes longer.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken divan
directions: Place broccoli in bottom of a greased casserole.
Put chicken on top of broccoli.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add salt and soda to milk, then add to creamed mixture.
Add flour gradually.
Chill for 1/2 hour.
Roll out on floured board about 1/4 inch thick.
Cut in desired shapes and bake on a greased pan at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix well and keep in jar away from moisture.
Add one or two tablespoons of powdered mix per cup.

title: seashell salad
directions: Cook baby shells as directed, drain and rinse in cold water. Combine with cheese, eggs and vegetables.
Blend salad dressing and pickle juice; toss with shells and vegetable mixture.

title: buckwheat cake
directions: The night before, dissolve the yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water. Sift the white flour and the buckwheat flour with the salt.
Blend the mixture.
In the morning, take out 1 cup of batter for a starter.
Then add molasses or syrup, soda, hot water and melted butter.
Then dissolve the syrup and soda in the hot water and butter.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook onion, pepper and celery in 1 stick of margarine.
Make 2 cups white sauce from 1 cup milk and 1 cup broth.
Thicken sauce with flour.
Mix all together with other ingredients.
Pour into oblong dish; top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Can add pimentos if desired.

title: double chocolate mud bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Beat together butter and sugar at medium speed until light and fluffy. Beat in egg yolks, one at a time, until blended.
Mix together flour, baking powder and salt.
Fold flour mixture into butter mixture.
Press mixture into prepared pan.
Pack down firmly. Sprinkle nuts, chocolate chips and marshmallows over the top of mixture in pan.
Beat egg whites at high speed until stiff peaks form.
Fold in brown sugar.
Spread over mixture in pan.
Bake for 35 minutes or until a crust is formed.
Transfer pan to a wire rack to cool completely.
Cut into squares.
Makes 36.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix together grated onions, rice, salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper, the egg and water; stuff peppers and replace tops.
Heat oil in a heavy saucepan; saute the chopped onions 10 minutes.
Mix in the tomatoes and the remaining pepper.
Arrange the peppers in an upright position.
Cover and cook over low heat for 45 minutes. Add the lemon juice and sugar; cook 30 minutes longer or until peppers are tender.
Baste frequently.
Gravy should be sweet and sour.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Start with 2 1/2 quarts of boiling water in a large pot.
Add oil and carrots.
Cook until tender, then add potatoes and onion. Cook until potatoes are almost done, then add chili, tomatoes, ketchup and sugar.
Cook for 10 minutes, then add other ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.
Put hamburger and sausage in last.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll out bread dough.
Spread butter on, leaving 1/4-inch dry all the way around edge.
Sprinkle on brown sugar, covering the butter.
Add the cinnamon on top of brown sugar.
Start at one end and roll to end.
Slice in about 1-inch thick pieces.
Place in well-greased pan.
Let rolls raise for about 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Remove from oven when brown and immediately turn over a platter or large plate.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 12 to 15 rolls.

title: green rice
directions: To boiling water, add rice and set aside.
Mix together egg, gravy, cheese, oil, pimentos, parsley, onion flakes and pepper. Fold in rice.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crab imperial
directions: Melt 1/4 cup margarine in heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add milk.
Cok over medium heat.
Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Fold in crabmeat.
Spoon into greased baking shells. Mix bread crumbs and margarine.
Sprinkle over crab mixture. Garnish with paprika.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: herbed tomato dressing for greens
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender, process until smooth. Makes 2 servings; 54 calories and 3 g fat per serving.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Put in blender as listed.
Blend on high speed until blended.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Stir in all ingredients.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and pineapple.
Bring to a boil and melt Jell-O. Remove from heat.
"Cool!!"
Add 1 large cottage cheese, 1 large Cool Whip and pecans.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish and chill 1 to 2 hours.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes.
Drain water off.
Peel potatoes and slice. Salt and pepper potatoes.
Add chopped onion.
Bring 2 quarts of water to a rolling boil.
Mix 2 cups vinegar and sugar with flour and eggs.
Beat until well blended.
Pour slowly in boiling water. Add drained fried bacon.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in a large pan.
Drain.
Add Ragu, tomato paste, canned tomatoes, water (if needed), garlic, Parmesan cheese, parsley and oregano.
Simmer together until thick.
Mix the Ricotta cheese and the beaten eggs.

title: john's pepper jelly
directions: Wash and dry peppers.
Cut in small pieces with seeds.
Place in blender with vinegar and puree until it looks like foam and has the texture of oatmeal.
Place in saucepan with sugar.
Bring to a boil and let simmer for 10 minutes.
Skim as desired.
Stir to make sure all the sugar is melted.
Pour in both packets of Certo. Let cool for 10 to 15 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
Put in jelly jars and keep in a cool place.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: stuffed pasta shells
directions: Cook noodles according to directions.
Mix cheeses, egg and spices together to use for stuffing.
Pour 1/2-inch of sauce into baking pan.
Stuff shells and place side by side in baking pan. Cover shells slightly with sauce and sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jew bread
directions: Mix the eggs, sugar and flour and cook over boiling water until sugar melts.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Pour into sheet cake pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until done.
Hope you enjoy this as much as I have.

title: caramel popcorn balls
directions: Combine popcorn and cereal in a large bowl; set aside.
In a heavy saucepan over low heat or in a microwave-safe dish, heat caramels and water until the caramels are melted.
Stir in peanuts and salt; mix well.
Pour over popcorn mixture and toss to coat. With buttered hands, shape into 3-inch balls.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix together in the
order
given.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Put
foil over the top if it browns too fast.

title: swiss string beans
directions: Thaw beans.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter in pan.
Add flour and stir in sour cream.
Cook until thick or bubbly; add onion, salt and pepper.
Fold in beans.
Place into 9-inch square casserole dish.
Add grated cheese to top and cover with bread crumbs.
Pour 1 tablespoon melted butter on top.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Double recipe for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Microwave: Grease 2-quart microwave-safe ring mold.
Place butter in 4-cup glass measure.
Microcook at 100% power for 1 minute.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and paprika until smooth. Blend in milk.
Cover tightly with Saran Wrap, turning back edge to vent.
Microwave at 100% power for 5 minutes, until thickened, sirring twice.
Layer potatoes and onion slices alternately in prepared mold, starting and ending with potatoes.
Pour sauce over potatoes and sprinkle with paprika.
Cover dish tightly with Saran Wrap, turning back edge to vent.
Microwave at 50% power about 25 minutes or until potatoes are fork-tender, rotating dish twice. Let stand on heatproof surface for 5 minutes before serving.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Start with 4 drops flavoring, then carefully add flavoring and color as desired.
Knead until pie dough consistency.
Add sugar to make softer or decrease sugar for firmer consistency.
Take small pinch and roll in sugar. Press into mold, unmold onto wax paper.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix sugar and softened butter together.
Add egg yolks and vanilla.
Mix.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Top with meringue.

title: easy puff pastry
directions: Bring to a boil water and butter.
Add flour gradually.
Turn off heat and beat until it forms a ball.
One at a time, beat in eggs until mixture is smooth.
With frosting tip, make a hole in Ziploc quart size bag.
Fill bag with dough.
Form puffs to the desired size.
Bake at 325°; do not brown too much.
Cool.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: russian salad
directions: Dissolve jello, miniature marshmallows, cream cheese and water.
Let cool.
Add pecans, mayonnaise, pineapple with juice and milk.
Chill until firm and keep refrigerated.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add bananas and eggs.
Sift flour; re-sift three times after adding salt, baking powder and soda. Add to banana mixture.
Add nuts last.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: texas hash
directions: Saute onions in shortening until brown.
Add beef and brown. Stir in green pepper, salt, pepper, chili powder and rice.
Place peas in center of mixture.
Pour tomatoes over all.
Cover; bring to boil.
Reduce heat to simmer and cook 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: four-layer dessert
directions: Put on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water for 5 minutes.
Add sugar, salt and egg.
Mix well.
Add 2 cups flour; beat until mixed.
Add rest of flour gradually.
Knead several minutes.
Store in refrigerator.
Two hours before baking, shape into rolls.
Cover and let rise for 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: brown bread
directions: Mix flour, All-Bran, sugar and salt.
Add raisins, nuts, then soda to sour milk.
Add molasses and sour milk to dry ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased cans.
Use two (No. 2) cans, like corn or peas come in.
This recipe makes 2 loaves.
After it is done, take a knife around the can and hit the bottom of can and it should come out.

title: chicken pie
directions: Arrange a layer of chicken and a layer Veg-All.
Pour broth over this.
Mix flour, milk and oleo together.
Pour this mixture over top of chicken and Veg-All.
Bake in oven at 400° for about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: eggplant with tomato sauce(great over rice)
directions: Cook diced eggplant 10 minutes or until tender and water is almost absorbed.
Put sauteed onions and chopped green peppers in skillet, add juice of tomatoes and let boil gently until reduced about half in amount.
Cut tomatoes in small pieces and add seasonings.
Add cubed eggplant.
Mix well and let simmer a few minutes to absorb flavor.
Sauce should be quite thick.
If you use too many onions it will be thinner, but still very good.

title: sweet and sour brisket
directions: Season brisket to taste with garlic powder, salt and pepper. Place sliced onions on bottom of roaster.
Put in brisket.
Mix preserves and catsup; pour over brisket.
Bake, covered, for 4 hours at 350° or until tender.
Makes about 24 servings.

title: macaroni and tomatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat until bubbly.
Serve hot.

title: squash casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tin can dogs
directions: Slice hot dog so that it will open like a book and insert thin slices of cheese (you name it).
Then place hot dog with cheese toward the hinge end of the bun.
This keeps the cheese from running too much.
Wrap in foil and place in preheated oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
After removing hot dog from the foil, you will probably have to eat it with a fork because this really is a hot dog.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients (except cheese and potato chips). Mix well. Pour into buttered casserole. Top with cheese and potato chips. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, margarine and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating after each.
Add flour and baking powder.
Mix together alternately with milk, 1 teaspoon at a time.
Add vanilla.
Stir in crushed pineapple and juice.

title: ranch bacon and cheddar cheese dip
directions: Stir dip mix into sour cream.
Add bacon bits and cheddar cheese.
Mix together and chill 1 hour before serving.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Pop popcorn and set aside.
Mix all ingredients, stirring often over low heat until coming to a boil.
Remove from heat. Add food coloring if desired.
Pour over popcorn.
Butter hands and form balls with mixture.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Blend in milk, butter and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine remaining ingredients (1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar and 4 tablespoons cocoa).
Pour hot water over top. Do not stir.
Bake 40 minutes or until center is set.
Let stand 15 minutes.

title: fruit topping
directions: In a saucepan, combine ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Simmer, stirring constantly, for 1 to 2 minutes or until clear and thickened.
Serve warm over waffles.
Contains 10 calories per tablespoon.

title: tamale corn casserole
directions: Mix together well all ingredients and pour into a casserole dish and bake at 350° about one hour or until knife tip inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Melt butter and saute onion and pepper until white.
Mix everything together in bowl.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: taco oven fries(children's)
directions: Combine French fries and butter in bowl and mix well. Sprinkle taco mix over French fries.
Arrange in single layer on baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until browned.

title: hungarian veal goulash
directions: Saute meat in hot oil.
Add onion.
Saute 5 to 10 minutes, until almost all oil is gone.
Add paprika; stir, then add flour. Cook 5 minutes, blending well.
Place caraway seed, bay leaf and parsley in cheesecloth and add to pot with beef broth and puree. Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer 1 hour, or until meat is tender. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Discard seasoning bag.
(Half cup sour cream may be added just before serving.)
Is good over hot noodles.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Spoon over two or three pounds boneless chicken breasts and bake 45 minutes at 375°.
This serves 4 to 6.

title: sauteed salmon steaks
directions: Combine butter, soy sauce and garlic powder.
Heat oil in medium skillet; add salmon steaks and baste with butter mixture. Cook about 5 minutes or until browned on one side.
Turn, baste and place lemon slices on steaks.
Cook until salmon flakes when tested with a fork.
Makes 2 servings.

title: chicken salad supreme
directions: Mix the chicken, celery, grapes, almonds, parsley and salt. Toss with mayonnaise. Fold in whipped cream.

title: scalloped asparagus
directions: Butter casserole dish.
First, layer asparagus, then half of the eggs, then mushroom soup, thinned with very little liquid from asparagus.
Sprinkle with half of the almonds.
Then repeat. Sprinkle with fine cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter and bake at 300° to 350° until golden brown.
Serves 2 to 4 people.

title: quick tortilla pizza
directions: On paper towel or microwave-safe plate, microwave tortilla on High 1 minute. Spread pizza sauce over top to within 1/2-inch of edge.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and sprinkle lightly with oregano.

title: watergate pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Place cut cabbage in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour milk on top.
Put dressing mix on top (complete box).
Cut margarine in different pieces and place on top of stuffing mix.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour with pan covered with foil; bake an additional 1/2 hour uncovered.
Bake on middle rack.

title: chili beefburgers for a crowd
directions: Mix meat, quick oats, milk and seasonings.
Allowing 1/4 cup for each patty, shape into balls and flatten.
Slice onions. Place meat patties and onion slices on
a greased grill or in a greased skillet. Brush with melted margarine.
Broil 4 to 5 minutes. Turn and cook the other side the same way. Split and toast rolls. Place 1 meat patty, topped with onion slice, in each roll and spoon 2 tablespoons chile con carne over it.
Makes 25 sandwiches.

title: special corn bread
directions: Combine baking mix, cornmeal and sugar in mixing bowl.
Add eggs and milk; beat until well blended.
Mix in melted butter. Pour into a greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until toothpick comes out dry.

title: lemon tea
directions: Steep tea in hot water for 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags; add to the rest of the ingredients and stir.
Can be used hot or cold.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Grate carrots and zucchini.
Slice scallions.
Combine flour, baking powder, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Beat together the egg, milk, carrots, zucchini and scallion.
Stir wet ingredients into dry until just combined.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a frying pan over medium heat.
Pour batter by tablespoonfuls into pan, making a few pancakes at a time.
Cook until golden, about 2 minutes on each side.
Add remaining oil to pan as needed. Serve at once.

title: mystery fruit cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix the dates, raisins, cherries and pecans. Add crumbled up cake mix and frosting mix.
Mix well until moist. Press into a foil lined buttered pan; a Bundt pan is nice. Refrigerate for 24 hours before using.
Keeps a long time in refrigerator.

title: crock pot meat loaf
directions: Combine ground beef, eggs, oats, soup mix and ketchup, reserving 2 tbsp of ketchup. Put in crock pot, top with reserved ketchup. Cover; cook on low 8-10 hours or on high for 4-6 hours. 8 servings.

title: hawaiian lumpia(makes 60)
directions: Note:
Need 90 square wrappers (found in the freezer section).

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Use medium-sized mushrooms.
Remove stems, chop and combine with bread, onions, cheese, salt, pepper, paprika and 1 tablespoon oil.
Stuff the mushrooms, pour remaining oil into baking dish and tilt to spread evenly.
Heat the pan in a 375° oven, then arrange mushrooms in it.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: crunchy punch
directions: Boil jello and sugar together until clear.
You may use any flavor jello that you like, add the juices to the jello and sugar. Mix well and freeze.
Remove from freezer, let stand at room temperature until crunchy.
Add 1 to 2 quarts of ginger ale just before serving.
You can prepare this ahead of time and you don't have to bother with ice.
Serves 35 to 40.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, pumpkin and soda.
Mix in all remaining ingredients; stir well.
Drop from teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 9 dozen.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze out liquid.
Mix sour cream and mayonnaise.
Add soup mix to sour cream and mayonnaise.
Chop chestnuts and onions into small pieces.
Mix everything together in large bowl.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Chill.
Cut top off the French bread round; take out bread and cut into pieces.
Set aside.
Fill round with spinach dip; use pieces for dipping.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, pecans, and apples and let set 1 hour.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Grease and flour 1 tube pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350 for one hour and 15 minutes.
Test at 1 hour. Loaf pans may take less time.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Blend well.
Serve with chips and vegetables.

title: cavatelli with broccoli
directions: Melt butter and heat garlic in large frying pan.
Add broccoli.
Cover and cook until desired tenderness.
Pour over cooked cavatelli.

title: chocolate chip meringue drops
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Line a baking sheet with foil and set aside.

title: spinach dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add vegetable mix, chopped sliced water chestnuts and 3/4 cup chopped green onions and add to mixture along with remaining ingredients.
Mix and refrigerate 1 hour.

title: corn flake bars
directions: Bring to boil the first 4 ingredients.
Pour over corn flakes and coconut.
Mix and press into a buttered pan.
Use butter on your hands to press firmly into pan.
Refrigerate; cut into bars.

title: bacon, avocado and sour cream soup
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain on paper towels.

title: cinderella crisps
directions: Using two forks, roll bread strips in condensed milk, coating all sides.
Roll in coconut.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove at once.
Makes 24.

title: peachy cinnamon coffeecake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 8-inch square pan.
Drain peaches; reserve juice.
Add milk to reserved juice to equal 3/4 cup liquid.
Chop peaches.

title: zucchini stew
directions: Brown meat, onions and garlic.
Add all ingredients except spaghetti and zucchini; cook 2 hours.
Add spaghetti and zucchini.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain noodles and add noodles to tuna, soup and vegetables in a casserole dish. Heat at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: bacon and egg wraps
directions: In a nonstick skillet, saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender. In a bowl, beat the eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Pour over vegetables in skillet. Sprinkle with cheese and bacon. Cover and stir gently over medium heat until the eggs are completely set. Spoon 1/2 cup into the center of each tortilla; fold sides over filling. Serve with salsa, if desired.

title: *baked broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli as package directs and drain thoroughly.
Beat eggs in mixing bowl.
Stir in celery soup, Cheddar cheese soup and mayonnaise.
Place drained broccoli in shallow baking dish.
Spoon egg mixture over the broccoli.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: dad's delicious chocolate chips
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugars.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add wheat germ, salt, baking soda, oatmeal, peanut butter and flour and stir.
Gently stir in nuts and chips.
Drop spoonfuls of batter onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° preheated oven for 10 minutes or until cookies are done.

title: peter's pot casserole
directions: Combine
all
ingredients and cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered,
in
x
13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat egg yolks, add buttermilk, sugar and butter.
Mix well. Beat flour with sweet milk.
Add lemon flavoring to the mixture. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: presto pesto pasta(serves 2)
directions: Bring water to boil in large pot.
Place noodles in boiling water; stir.
Allow to cook, uncovered, until firm and tender. About 4 to 5 minutes before noodles are done, add peas.
Allow to return to boiling.

title: deep fried squirrel
directions: Clean and wash squirrels thoroughly.
Cut up.
Shake in plastic, covered bowl of flour until all pieces of squirrel are covered good.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Wash chicken and dip in egg.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Cook chicken in skillet of melted butter on medium heat, turning occasionally (takes approximately 20 minutes).
After chicken is done, pour spaghetti sauce over and cover.
Let simmer 5 minutes. Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top, let melt and serve.

title: born again cookies(ephesians 2:8)
directions: Beat egg, sugar and extract until thick.
Add nuts and flour, gradually, folding in after each addition.
Drop by teaspoonful 2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: cheddar baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes for 1 hour at 400° or until done.
Cut hot potatoes in half lengthwise.
Scoop out potatoes and save the shells.
In a mixing bowl, mash the potatoes.
Add butter, cream, onion and salt.
Beat until fluffy.
Mix in 1/2 cup cheese.
Divide into shells and sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Serves 6.

title: molasses fried chicken
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix water and molasses.
Dip chicken in molasses, then in flour mixture.
Dip again in molasses and again in flour mixture.
Fry in hot oil just until brown on each side. Place on a rack in a baking pan and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
