title: fruit-n-juice breakfast shake
directions: Break banana into small pieces and put in blender with other ingredients.
Blend until smooth.
Divide shake between 2 glasses and serve immediately.

title: southern lights sweet potato souffle
directions: In mixing bowl, mash potatoes.
Beat with electric mixer to remove all lumps.
Beat in margarine.
Beat in egg substitute until consistency is smoother, about 5 minutes.
Stir in sugar or honey, orange juice concentrate, milk, ginger, pecans, citrus rinds and salt.
In metal or glass bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into potato mixture.
Pour batter into 2-quart souffle dish or casserole sprayed with nonstick vegetable coating. Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Souffle is done when skewer inserted in center comes out clean.
It will not puff up like a dessert souffle.
(Makes eight 1-cup servings.)
Each serving contains approximately (original recipe):
450 calories; 192 mg. cholesterol; 18 mg. fat; 95 mg. sodium.

title: shirley lavy's hot ham and cheese sandwiches
directions: Melt margarine.
Saute onion until soft or add dried onions. Add Worcestershire sauce, poppy seed and mustard.
Blend well. Spread on both sides of buns.
Add ham and cheese.
Wrap with foil and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese is melted. These can be made ahead of time and can also be frozen.
These are a favorite and I think of Shirley when I make them.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all together as corn bread.
Bake at 400° or 425° in iron skillet or pan.

title: yellow squash patties
directions: Saute one med size onion.
Grate 3 med size squash with skins and mix with 1/2 stick crushed Ritz crackers and 1 T flour and pinch of salt. Then add 1 beaten egg and stir well.
Fry in hot skillet and drop onto paper towels to drain.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Add cubed apples and black walnuts.
Sift together flour, salt and soda 3 times.
Add flavoring.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place in greased loaf or tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°, starting in cold oven.

title: jam squares
directions: Combine all ingredients except preserves in mixing bowl.

Beat at low speed until mixture is crumbly. Reserve 2 cups mixture; press remaining onto bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Spread preserves evenly over base; sprinkle with reserved mixture. Bake in preheated 400° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown. Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: ham and egg bake
directions: Using a small glass, cut 12 circles out of 12 slices of bread. Break up the leftover bread and add to greased 9 x 13 pan.
Top with ham and cheese.
Butter the bread circles and put them, buttered side up, over cheese.
Beat eggs, milk and salt and pour over top. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour, uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.
Let it sit up to 10 minutes before serving.
A rope of keilbasa, cut across and then in quarters, can be used instead of ham.

title: banana muffins
directions: Combine cereal, milk and bananas. Add egg and shortening. Beat well. Combine flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add to banana mixture, stirring only until flour mixture is moistened. Add flavorings.
Stir, but do not beat.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: salmon dip
directions: Take out bones.
Make a paste.
Beat cheese until smooth.
Add salmon, lemon juice, seasoning and fromage; mix well.
Divide equally between 4 custard cups.
Smooth the surfaces.
Slice and decorate with pickles.

title: meat boats
directions: Cut slice from top of rolls.
Hollow out center of each roll; reserve crumbs for meat mixture.
Season softened butter with garlic salt and spread on rolls.
Saute onion and green peppers in 1 tablespoon butter.
Soften bread crumbs in soup and egg.
Mix all together and fill rolls.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. These can be frozen and cooked later.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion for 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Combine soup and sour cream; add all vegetables to this.
Pour melted margarine over herb seasoned dressing and mix well.
Put half of this in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole which has been sprayed with nonstick spray.
Pour soup and vegetable mixture over dressing and top with other half of seasoned dressing.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lie's baked beans
directions: Boil beans 1/2 hour (save water).
Place pork and onions in crock-pot.
Add Gravy Master, spices and sugar, then beans. Add water, enough to cover.
Cook on high.
Start around 10:00 a.m. to be ready for dinner. These beans are wonderful served with Johnny Cake.

title: donkey tails
directions: Make deep slits in the side of each hot dog and stuff with as much cheese as possible, about 6 tablespoons each. Halve the flour tortillas, then wrap each hot dog in a tortilla half. Secure ends with toothpicks. Heat oil in deep-fryer to 375°. Fry wrapped hot dogs a few at a time being careful not to crowd. Cook only 2 to 3 minutes or until tortillas are puffed and golden brown. Drain well and serve immediately with mustard-picante mixture. Makes 4 servings.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Arrange chicken, single layer, in an 8 x 10-inch baking dish. Mix soup mix and dressing and pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender.
Garnish chicken with apricot half on each piece.
Serve with rice.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and oleo until crumbly.
Save 1/2 mixture for topping.
To remaining mixture, add baking powder, salt, egg yolks and milk.
Beat 2 egg whites until stiff; fold into batter.
Pour into greased pan.
Sprinkle with blueberries and reserved topping. Bake at 350°.

title: kiss cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients, except Kisses. Mix on low speed until dough forms.
Shape dough into balls with a rounded teaspoonful.
Roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately press Kiss into cookie until it cracks.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: baked zucchini pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel and thinly slice zucchini and chop onion.
Saute zucchini and onion in margarine for about 10 minutes, or until tender; remove from heat.
Stir in spices. Separate rolls and press into pie plate.
In large bowl; blend eggs and cheese together.
Stir cooked zucchini mixture into eggs and cheese.
Pour into pie pan, and bake 30-40 minutes, or until lightly browned and set.
Let sit for 5-10 minutes.
Slice into wedges and serve.

title: quickie fudge(microwave)
directions: Blend together powdered sugar and cocoa in an 8 x 8-inch dish. Pour in milk.
Place butter on top.
Heat on High for 2 minutes, or until butter melts.
Stir well to mix ingredients.
Add vanilla and nuts; stir until blended.
Place in freezer for 20 minutes. Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Cut each wing and discard tips.
In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients and marinate for 2 hours or more.

title: easy bread sticks
directions: Melt butter. Cut buns in 4 strips. Dip in butter and season with garlic powder. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 1 hr. at 200°.

title: chili sauce
directions: Place hamburger in pan and cover with water-boil 20 minutes stirring often.
Add more water as it boils dry-add other ingredients and boil 30 minutes of until it cooks down to a sauce. Can be frozen.

title: beef potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes on bottom and sides of 8 x 12-inch dish.
Bake at 400°, uncovered for 10 minutes.
Brown ground beef and drain. Place beef, broccoli and half of onions and tomato in potato shell.
Combine soup, milk, 1/2 cup cheese and seasonings.
Pour over beef mixture.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake uncovered 2 to 3 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour and 3/4 cup pecans together.
Melt butter and pour over flour mixture; mix well.
Press into 13 x 9 x 1-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° until slightly browned; cool.
Blend cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1 1/4 cups Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Mix instant pudding with 4 cups milk.
Spread for third layer.
Top with 9 ounces Cool Whip and garnish with chopped pecans.
Store in refrigerator 4 hours or overnight before serving.

title: nanny's great cookies
directions: Place raisins and water in pan and boil for 3 minutes.
Set aside to cool; do not drain.
Mix dry ingredients.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Beat until well-blended.
Drop by teaspoonfuls, about 1 1/2 inches apart, onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Grease an 8-inch square pan.
Microwave chocolate chips and condensed milk uncovered in a 2 quart bowl on High for 2 minutes. Stir until smooth.
Stir in sugar and vanilla.
Pour into pan. Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.
(Nuts are optional.)

title: low sodium pie crust
directions: Blend shortening with flour.
Add water.
Roll pie crust.
All materials should be cold.
Handle pie crust as little as possible. Fill with any desired fruit, omitting salt.
Trace of sodium:
1/8 pie.
I got this recipe from St.
Luke's Hospital, Kansas City, Missouri.

title: chicken with peaches
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place chicken into shallow baking dish. Dot chicken with flour and margarine.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Open can of peaches and pour peaches and syrup over the chicken.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake for an additional 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Grease and flour pan.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt. In big bowl, beat peanut butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cherry surprises
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease tiny muffin tins and sprinkle chopped pecans in bottom of tins. Cream together brown sugar, granulated sugar and butter. Add egg yolks and vanilla extract and blend. Sift flour and baking powder together and add, blending well. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Place 1 teaspoon batter on top of nuts and press a whole maraschino cherry into center. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes and, while still warm, roll in confectioners sugar. Yield: 4 dozen tiny muffins.

title: quick cheesecake
directions: Soften cream cheese and blend all ingredients together. Pour into graham cracker pie crust. Top with fresh fruit or pie filling of choice.

title: picnic potatoes
directions: Halve potatoes lengthwise; cut each half crosswise into 1/2-inch slices.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter in skillet.
Arrange enough potato slices in skillet to cover bottom.
Season with 1/4 teaspoon salt and a dash of sugar and pepper.
Saute for 10 minutes or until golden on bottom side.
Turn with pancake turner.
Saute for 5 minutes or until golden.
Drain on paper towel and keep warm. Repeat until all potatoes are sauteed.
Cook onion in 2 tablespoons of butter until just tender.
Return all potatoes to skillet and garnish with onion rings.
Yields 6 servings.

title: richard's easy asparagus(microwave)
directions: In a microwave-safe bowl, place asparagus on bottom.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Dot top with butter.
Cover and microwave on Medium for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add cream cheese and stir gently until cream cheese is melted, and serve.

title: 5-layer yummy
directions: Mix with fingers until crumbly.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool 1 hour.

title: apple crisp
directions: Pare apples and slice very thin.
Blend sugar, flour and butter, keeping ingredients cold so that the resulting mixture will be crumbly.
Butter a casserole or baking pan.
Lay apples in it and sprinkle with cinnamon. Add the water and spread over the crumbly mixture. Bake, uncovered, in a moderate oven at 400° for about 50 minutes.
Serve with or without whipped cream.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix together and pour over macaroni and eggs.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in slices.
Arrange in greased cake pan.
In a bowl, combine salt, pepper, dry mustard and paprika.
Mix together and sprinkle over the sliced potatoes.
Melt butter and pour over all.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix flour, soda, salt and sugar.
Mash bananas and add eggs and milk.
Put a well in the center of the dry ingredients.
Add the bananas and mix.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fudge brownie pie with real hot fudge sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 325°f. 160°c. gas mark 3. In a double boiler melt the chocolate over 1 of hot, but not simmering water.
Remove chocolate from the heat and cool slightly.
Thoroughly stir together the flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
In a large bowl, using an electric mixer, beat the butter and sugar until blended, about 2 minutes.
Beat in the whole egg and the egg yolk, then beat in the vanilla.
Beat for 2-3 minutes until the batter is very light and fluffy and the sugar has dissolved.
Beat in the melted chocolate at low speed.
Stir in the dry ingredients until incorporated.

title: impossible pie
directions: Butter pie pan.
Mix ingredients and pour in pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: joyce's salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into large glass bowl and refrigerate overnight.
May also put into 9 x 13-inch dish and freeze for a frozen salad or dessert.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix and bake in a loaf pan at 325° to 350°.
Caution:
It will burn easily.
Bake 1 hour.
Cool thoroughly.

title: mint surprise cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients but wafers and walnuts. Mix at lowest speed on mixer until dough forms.
Press candy wafers into approximately 2 teaspoons dough and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Smooth edges. Top each with walnut half or pecan.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 12 minutes.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix all ingredients together, adding beaten eggs last.
Pour mixture into hot baking dish.
Bake at 325°.
When crusted on top and around edges, stir under and let crust form again.
Bake about 40 minutes.
Don't overbake; it might get too dry.
May be baked in microwave.

title: sherry thins
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg.
Add
sifted
dry ingredients alternately with sherry, beating until
smooth.
Wrap
dough
in foil and chill several hours or
overnight.
Roll	dough out thin on floured board or pastry cloth
and
cut
out
shapes with small cookie cutters. Put on cookie sheet; sprinkle with almonds or candies and bake at 400° for
8 to 10 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 7 dozen.
Contains 40 calories per serving.

title: yummy mandel bread
directions: Add eggs, one at a time, to sugar in bowl; mix well.
Add vanilla and oil and mix.
Add to dry ingredients in other bowl. Mix until smooth.
Shape into 4 or 5 loaves.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, until golden brown.
Take out of oven and slice with sharp knife and put back into oven for about another 5 to 10 minutes to dry center.

title: wet cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, soda, salt, eggs, nuts, 1 teaspoon vanilla and pineapple in a large mixing bowl with spoon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes, peel and dice.
Boil eggs and peel; chop.
Chop all other ingredients.
Mix all together.
Delicious served hot. (This recipe may also be refrigerated.)

title: spicy fruit bar
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, spices, water, oil and raisins. Boil 3 minutes and then set aside to cool.
Add combined dry ingredients, then add dates and apricots.
Spread in oiled 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 325° about 45 minutes; cool.

title: heavenly pies
directions: Combine condensed milk and lemon juice in bowl.
Add pineapple and walnuts; mix well.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into pie shells.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.
Yield:
18 servings.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute celery, onion and garlic in bacon drippings.
Brown hamburger meat.
Drain and add to sauteed mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 hour.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar together; pour into graham cracker crust.
Let chill for 1 hour.
Add fruit topping and serve.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Dissolve soda in milk.
Mix sugar and butter.
Add flour, cinnamon and wine.
Add milk and fruit.
Mix with hand.
Drop on greased pan.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: chicken chili stew
directions: Cut chicken into 1 inch pieces and cook in the oil with onion, garlic and green pepper until chicken is done (about 6 minutes).

title: artichoke nibbles
directions: Drain juice of one jar of hearts into frying pan; add onion and cook until tender.
In bowl, beat eggs and seasonings; mix well, then add cheese, hearts, onion and parsley.
Bake in an 8 x 10-inch pan for 30 minutes in preheated oven of 325°.
Let set for 10 minutes before slicing.

title: party cheese wreath
directions: Beat Cheddar cheese and cream cheese with electric mixer until well blended.
Add juice, bell pepper, onion, Worcestershire sauce and ground pepper; mix well.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Place drinking glass in center of serving platter. Drop round tablespoons of mixture to form ring around glass, just touching outer edge of glass; smooth with spatula.
Remove glass. Garnish with chopped fresh parsley and red pepper stars.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: double boiler pudding
directions: Toast bread and butter slices.
Cut in cubes.
Put sugar in top of double boiler; add bread, then add raisins.
Add milk to beaten eggs.
Pour over bread and raisins; do not stir.
Cover and put over bottom of double boiler which is half full of cold water. Set over heat and cook 1 hour with water boiling gently.
Turn out into serving dish and serve warm.
The brown sugar makes a sauce.

title: doughnuts
directions: Let the first 4 ingredients cool.
Add the next 3 ingredients to first cooled mixture.
When yeast is dissolved, add 3 or 4 cups flour.
Cover; set aside 1/2 hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let rise until double in size.
Cut out; let rise again.
Fry in hot lard.

title: coconut layer cake
directions: Sift together flour and baking powder.
Cream shortening; gradually add sugar, creaming until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk, add extract.
Pour into three greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Remove from oven; place on cake racks and let cool in pans.

title: easy fudge
directions: Bring sugar and milk to a boil and cook 7 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips, butter, vanilla, marshmallow cream and pecans.
Mix until everything is dissolved and pour onto a buttered cookie sheet.
Let harden 24 hours and cut into squares.

title: really good cabbage
directions: Cook (or steam) cabbage about 5 minutes until tender, but crisp.
Blend egg, vinegar, butter, sugar, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, until thick, about 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Cool slightly.
Add sour cream and pour over cabbage.
Toss well to coat.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: sin cake
directions: Mix together margarine, flour and nuts.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: sour cream dressing
directions: Mix thoroughly and add 1/4 cup finely cut fresh parsley. Blend and chill.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and corn meal in a large bowl.
Toss lightly with fork to mix.
Add eggs, butter, milk, lemon juice and lemon peel.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth and thoroughly blended.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 375° until golden brown.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat the margarine, sugar, egg, milk and vanilla together until light and fluffy.
Stir in the flour and baking powder, mixing well.
Chill dough thoroughly.

title: almond bark
directions: Toast almonds.
Cool.
Melt white chocolate.
Add flavoring and Crisco.
Add almonds.
Spread on a cookie sheet and cool. Break into pieces.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add more cracker crumbs if mixture is too wet.
Make into patties and fry until brown.
Serve hot.

title: red velvet cocoa cake(yummy!)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch round baking pans.
In a large bowl, beat butter, sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Add eggs and food color; blend well.

title: quick bread sticks
directions: Quarter buns (lengthwise).
Combine remaining ingredients in small bowl; mix.
Spread butter/herb mixture on cut side of buns. Place on two cookie sheets.
Bake at 250° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until crisp.

title: creamed vegetables
directions: In saucepan, melt butter over low heat.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk.
Heat to boiling for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Stir vegetables into sauce.
Heat through and serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hash brown pancakes
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add potatoes and beat in with a spoon until smooth.
Stir in milk.
Sift dry ingredients and stir in.
Beat egg whites until stiff and add into the rest.
For thinner pancakes, add up to 1/2 cup more milk.
Bake on lightly greased griddle.
Makes about 16 pancakes.
Very light and tender.

title: golden pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, combine brown sugar, flour, corn syrup, eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Stir in oleo and pecans.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes or until center of pie is firm and pie is golden brown.

title: chocolate chip zucchini cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Sprinkle top with chocolate chips. Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: spanish pork chops
directions: Grease a 10 or 12-inch frying pan.
Brown pork chops on 1 side and season to taste.
Cook rice while starting pork chops.
Turn chops and season.
Drain rice.
Place a 1/4 to 1/2-inch slice of onion on each chop.
Spoon on rice.
Add 1 whole tomato on each onion.
Add more tomatoes if you want more juice.
Add more seasoning if desired.
Cover pand and simmer for 45 minutes.
Test with fork and simmer longer if necessary.
Serves 4.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Combine pineapple, sugar and flour.
Stir.
Add melted
butter over mixture.
Crumble crackers on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: no bake treats(good for kids to make)
directions: Mix together peanut butter, powdered sugar, milk and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in oats and remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: chicken pie
directions: Rinse chicken.
Cook in water to cover until tender.
Bone and chop chicken; reserve 1 1/2 cups chicken broth.
Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine reserved broth, peas and soup in bowl; mix well.
Pour over chicken.
Stir flour into butter in bowl.
Add buttermilk; mix well.
Spoon over casserole.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: grandma linda's cake
directions: In medium mixing bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking soda, nutmeg, salt and cloves; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, beat butter with electric beaters on medium speed for 30 seconds. Add eggs, bananas, undrained pineapple and vanilla; beat until combined.
Add flour mixture.
Beat on low speed until mixed; beat on medium speed for 1 minute.
Fold in pecans.
Spread batter in well greased and floured 10-inch fluted tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 70 to 75 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove cake from pan; cool completely.
After cooled you may sprinkle with powdered sugar. Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: pepper and bean casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for about 1 1/2 hours.
Stir every 1/2 hour as top beans tend to dry out.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies and place half in bottom of dish.
Mix pudding mixes with milk.
Mix soft cream cheese, margarine and confectioners sugar.
Combine these two mixtures with Cool Whip. Pour over cookies.
Add the rest of the cookies to the top. Refrigerate.
Enjoy!!

title: vegetable supreme
directions: Mix together and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef and onions in electric skillet.
Add salt and pepper with Worcestershire sauce.
Arrange noodles on top of meat. Pour tomato juice over noodles and press lightly with spatula to moisten all noodles.
Cover and simmer 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy fresh peach cobbler
directions: Cut a thin-skinned orange through the skin, around the circumference, carefully so as not to touch the fruit.
With a teaspoon handle, turn the skin back until it forms a cup.

Do this at both ends and you have a peeled orange with a cup at each end. Place one cup on your plate, pour some brandy in upper cup, put lump of sugar in the brandy, light the brandy and stir gently as it burns.
Drink it when the flame dies.
She'll say, "Heavenly."

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, water and corn syrup together in a 2 1/2-quart saucepan until it forms a thread. Add raw peanuts, stirring continuously until mixture turns light brown. Remove from heat. Add soda and stir well. Spread on buttered cookie sheet. Let cool, then break apart.

title: karla j's tortilla pinwheels
directions: Usually double this recipe.
Mix all ingredients until blended.
Divide and spread on tortillas and roll up.
Cover in plastic wrap tightly and chill at least 4 to 5 hours or overnight. Cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Serve on a platter with a cup of salsa.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Note:
I use self-rising flour and omit salt and baking soda.

title: peanut crisp bars
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and salt in saucepan. Cook and stir until sugar is dissolved. Blend in peanut butter; stir in Rice Krispies. Pat evenly into 11 x 7 x 2 pan. In small saucepan, melt butter and brown sugar. Remove from heat; add milk and vanilla. Stir in powdered sugar and beat until smooth. Spread frosting and cut in small pieces. This is very sweet.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple; set aside (keeping pineapple juice).

title: caramel dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and margarine; then whip together until well blended.
Add brown sugar and blend well.

title: chocolate almond carrot ring
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Beat sugar and oil at medium speed of electric mixer until well mixed.
Stir in flour mixture.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in carrots, nuts, raisins and 2/3 cup of the coconut.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch Bundt pan or 6 cup ring mold.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes. Remove from pan.
Finish cooling.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain.
While still hot, add butter, onion and eggs.
Add bread crumbs and milk.
Stir.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts in water (put in a little salt).
Save broth.
Melt butter and add to dressing.
Stir.

title: creole bouillabaisse
directions: Cut fish into cubes.
In Dutch oven, melt butter.
Add olive oil.
Blend in flour.
Cook, stirring constantly, until light brown.
Add onions, celery and garlic.
Cook until onions begin to brown.
Gradually stir in water.
Add tomatoes, wine, parsley, lemon juice, bay leaf, salt, saffron, pepper and 1/4 of the fish. Bring to a boil.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add remaining fish and cook 5 to 8 minutes.
Add shrimp, oysters and crabmeat.
Cook another 5 minutes or until fish is done.

title: popcorn cake(a festive party dessert)
directions: Melt vegetable oil, margarine and marshmallows.
Pour over peanuts, popcorn and candy in large bowl.
Blend with hands; pack into buttered pan (Bundt pan looks best).

title: glorified rice
directions: Serves 6 to 8.

title: saucy vegetable baked potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Use 1 tablespoon oil to rub on all 8 potatoes.

Bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done. Blend remaining 3 tablespoons oil, flour and pepper in a large saucepan until smooth. Stir in milk gradually. Cook and stir on medium or medium-high heat until mixture comes to a boil and is slightly thickened and smooth. Remove from heat. Stir in cheese until melted.
Stir in vegetables.
(Reheat on low, if necessary.) Cut open potatoes. Top with vegetables and sauce.
Makes 8 servings.

title: molasses ginger drops
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cream shortening; beat in sugar.
Stir in molasses.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in dry ingredients and nuts.
Drop onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 60.

title: pineapple-coconut chess pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a bowl; add eggs and vanilla. Stir until blended.
Stir in butter, coconut and pineapple.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until sets.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Melt margarine in a pan (about 3 or 4-quart pan).
Add applesauce, Equal and cinnamon; mix together good with apples. Peel and cut apples into medium cubes.

title: chip kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add salt and cream of tartar. Continue beating until stiff, but not dry.
Add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating thoroughly.
Fold in nuts, chocolate, vanilla and/or other flavor.
Drop onto cookie sheet (teaspoon size).
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.
Watch carefully. Should be very lightly browned.
Yield: about 72 kisses.

title: marinade
directions: Mix all together and marinate meat at least 6 hours.
This is good with chicken, London Broil, pork chops, sword fish steaks, etc.
Marinade also freezes well.

title: fruit kuchen
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix sugar, milk, vanilla and slightly beaten eggs.
Stir in flour mixture.
Spread onto a greased cookie sheet which has sides on it.
Arrange fruit evenly over batter.

title: cider syrup
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon in a small saucepan. Stir in apple cider and lemon juice. Cook and stir the mixture over a medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat and stir in butter until melted. Makes about 1 1/3 cups.

title: cheddar bay biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix Bisquick, milk and cheese until a soft dough forms.
Drop by spoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown. Mix butter and garlic powder.
Brush mixture over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.

title: hamburg dinner in foil
directions: Divide hamburger into 4 portions.
Cut foil pieces, 12 inches each.
Loosen hamburg apart and place each portion in the center of foil.
Divide chopped vegetables and place on top of hamburg, then sprinkle each with a pat of butter.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Heat electric skillet to hot, 400°.
Shake chicken in a bag with the flour, salt and chicken seasoning.
Place in hot Crisco, be careful not to get burned from splatters.
Turn often until golden brown.
Turn heat to 350°.
Cover and cook for 25 to 30 minutes.
Turn one time during cooking.
Remove from Crisco and place on paper towel to drain.

title: elna's congealed salad
directions: Heat pineapple and add Jell-O; cool until thickened.
Cream cottage cheese and pimento.
Add to first mixture.
Add nuts and celery.
Whip the cream and fold into mixture.
Chill.

title: orange candy fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Alternately add flour and soda that has been dissolved in buttermilk.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well and put into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: grandma houser's slaw
directions: Grate cabbage, onion and carrots; mix together in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with celery seed and sugar.
Add vinegar and oil; mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: beef noodle soup
directions: Boil meat with bay leaf, onions and salt until meat is tender. Remove meat, strain broth.
Add water to make 1 gallon of broth. Add beef bouillon if needed for extra flavor.
Bring to boil; add noodles.
Cook approximately 10 minutes.
Cube meat, add to soup and bring back to boil.
May add a drop of Kitchen Bouquet for color.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Combine bacon, onion and green pepper.
Cook over medium heat until bacon is lightly browned and onion and pepper are tender. Drain.
Combine bacon mixture and remaining ingredients; mix well. Bake in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish, uncovered, at 425° for 30 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Mix sugar and flour, then add the rest of ingredients to melted butter/dish. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut buster dessert
directions: Mix flour and butter like pie crust.
Add peanuts and spread in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.
Set aside until cool.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Place chopped apples in pie shell. Combine flour, sugar and salt in a bowl. Add sour cream, egg and vanilla. Beat until smooth.
Pour mixture over apples. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.
Remove from oven and add the following crumb topping.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Heat butter until it becomes light brown.
Remove from heat. Beat in sugar, milk, vanilla and salt.
Stir in peanut butter.
If mixture becomes too heavy, add warm milk or water to make it of spreading consistency.

title: play dough for kids
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients.
Add liquids and knead well as it becomes cool enough to touch.
Store in covered container or plastic bag in the refrigerator.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients in mayonnaise (if needed).
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: muffin divan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine chicken, mushrooms, sauce, salad dressing and onion.
Mix lightly.
Top muffin halves with chicken mixture and broccoli.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 10 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Continue baking until cheese begins to melt.
Make 6 sandwiches.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening, sugar and salt.
Blend and cool.
Add eggs.
Let yeast stand in warm water for 5 minutes, then stir and add to mixture.
Add flour.
Blend well.
Cover and place in refrigerator for at least 4 hours.
Dough will keep for several days.

If frozen, about 3 hours before using, roll into shapes as desired, using enough flour to make them easy to handle. Place in greased pans and allow to rise in room of moderate temperature until double original size.
If not frozen, 2 hours before using.
Bake at 350° or 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: new orleans bread pudding
directions: Beat sugar, eggs, vanilla and salt.
Scald milk and butter. Break 3 pieces white bread in small pieces into glass loaf pan. Mix milk with egg mixture.
Pour over bread.
Place in pan of water.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.
Serve warm with whipped cream or even better with caramel sauce!

title: angel hair pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed.
Toss all ingredients in bowl and chill.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans.
Mix with soup and 1/2 of onion rings.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Turn oven off.
Add remaining onion rings.
Return to hot oven for 5 minutes.

title: all saints eggs and sausage
directions: Brown meat, drain on paper towel.
Mix eggs, milk and seasonings.
Stir in bread, cheese and sausage.
Pour in buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Refrigerate, covered overnight.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.
Great breakfast for a gang!

title: chop beef spread
directions: May use a little garlic salt or garlic.

title: cranberry-apple salad
directions: Grate orange peel on coarse grater to make long shreds, about 2 tablespoons (optional).
Peel oranges; cut oranges into 1/2-inch cubes.
Wash and drain cranberries; remove any stems.
Using blender, chop cranberries.
In medium bowl, combine the grated orange peel, cubed oranges, cranberries and sugar; mix well. Refrigerate until well chilled, several hours.

title: chex party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Melt butter in open roasting pan.
Stir in seasonings and gradually stir in cereals, nuts, pretzels and tidbits.
Mix to coat evenly.
Bake for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: date-nut oatmeal drops
directions: Pour water over dates in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until dates are soft.
Stir to make a paste, then beat in the oil. Stir in shredded apple, vanilla and salt.
Add oats and nuts; blend, then let stand 10 minutes to absorb the moisture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until golden brown, watching closely.
Makes 36.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onions, celery and broccoli in butter for 3 to 5 minutes. Stir in cheese, soup and milk until smooth. Stir in rice. Place in casserole and top with cheese. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream the peanut butter and cream cheese. Add Cool Whip and sugar until well mixed.
Pour into a graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: party chicken sandwiches
directions: Combine chicken, salad dressing, chilies, cheese and onion. Mix lightly.
Cover bread with chicken mixture.
Broil 5 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve hot.

title: buckeyes
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter in a pan.
Mix with powdered sugar.
Roll into balls.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips and pour over peanut butter balls.

title: banana nut gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add cold water and stir. Chill the gelatin in refrigerator until it begins to firm.
Stir in the applesauce, banana and walnuts.
Makes 4 (1/2-cup) servings.
Make the night before, if desired.

title: "farmer's" rice pudding
directions: Put rice, sugar and cinnamon in bowl and stir thoroughly.
Add 1/2 of milk and mix well.
Add vanilla and rest of milk, stir thoroughly; sprinkle with cinnamon, if desired.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions.
Fold in Cool Whip.
In large bowl, put a layer of vanilla wafers, a layer of cut up bananas, then a layer of pudding mix.
Repeat several times, ending with the pudding mix.

title: corn relish
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Add vinegar and water, stirring until smooth.
Add onion.
Cook over medium heat stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat, stir in corn, green pepper and pimiento.
Cover and chill.

title: bologna candy
directions: Boil sugar and half and half to a soft ball on candy thermometer; add dates and continue to boil until mixture separates from the side of pan.
Add nuts, remove from heat and continue to stir until thick.
Pour mixture on a damp cloth and roll like bologna, then slice when cool.

title: snowballs
directions: Mix in large bowl chocolate chips, marshmallow cream and salt. Combine sugar and evaporated milk and stir until boils.
Boil for 6 minutes.
Remove from heat and add oleo and vanilla.
Pour over mixture in bowl.
Blend and set in warm water as you work.

title: raisin sweet bread
directions: Heat milk.
Add shortening, sugar and salt.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
When lukewarm, add yeast, mixed with warm water and eggs.
Put all into large bowl and beat in 2 cups flour until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour, a cup at a time, to make a soft dough.
Add raisins.

title: ruth's yum yum cake
directions: Pour fruit and juice in bottom of oblong cake pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix over top of fruit. Drizzle oleo or butter over top and sprinkle with coconut and nuts, if desired. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until top is golden brown. Serve warm with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: doritos casserole
directions: Place hamburger in casserole dish and add next 3 ingredients in saucepan and cook until bubbly.
Pour over hamburger.
Put the chips on top and then top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 400° until cheese is melted.
Also is great when you add sour cream on top when done.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Bake uncovered 45 minutes at 350°.

title: irish potato candy
directions: Cook, peel and mash one medium potato; add powdered sugar (enough to make a stiff dough).
Roll out and spread with peanut butter.
Roll as a jelly roll.
Roll the candy in powdered sugar. Chill, then slice.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, mustard and vinegar thoroughly and add to first 7 ingredients.
Chill.

title: lemon icebox pie(a very old recipe)
directions: In a large bowl, mix together 3 egg yolks and 1/2 cup lemon juice.
Stir in 1 can milk.
Fill pie plate with layer of crushed vanilla wafers.
Line side of entire plate with vanilla wafers standing.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Spread cream cheese on ham slices. Roll up. Secure with wooden toothpicks. Chill until serving time. Cut into 1/2-inch pieces.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together 1 1/2 cups sugar and 4 tablespoons margarine.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa.
Add this to creamed mixture; blend well and spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fruit smoothie
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender. Blend until smooth. Serve immediately.

title: pecan brittle
directions: Pecans should be heated but not cooked in warm oven before added to candy mixture.

title: chicken rice and mushroom dish
directions: Mix rice with 3 cups wate rand dry onion soup.
Line bottom of 9 x 11-inch glass pan with rice mixture.
Layer chicken over this. Cover with cream of mushroom soup.
(Optional:
Add fresh mushrooms.)
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes at 350°.
Add water, so rice won't dry out, if needed.

title: watergate salad
directions: Fix pudding as directed on package.
Cut up cherries and pineapple into small pieces and fold into pudding mix.
Fold in Cool Whip until completely smooth.
Add pecans and mini marshmallows.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: gingered carrots
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Cook, covered, 20 to 30 minutes or until carrots are tender, stirring occasionally.

title: chicken and rice dinner
directions: Cook chicken breasts and save broth; cube chicken.
Place onion and celery in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Cover with cooked rice.
Place cubed chicken over rice.
Mix mayonnaise, soups and broth.
Pour over chicken and rice.
Garnish with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 375° until bubbly.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook onion and broccoli in chicken broth until nearly tender. Heat margarine in pan.
Add flour; add milk and stir with wire whip until it starts to thicken.
Add broccoli and onion.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Do not boil; it will scorch the milk.
Add 1/2 cup cut up cheese.

title: garlic knots(low-cal)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.

Unroll dough and cut in half crosswise, then cut each half into ten 1-inch wide strips, making 20 strips. Tie each strip of dough into a loose knot and arrange on nonstick baking sheet, leaving about 1-inch space between each knot.
Set aside.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Cut vegetables in small pieces.
Layer in order given in large bowl.
Sprinkle with 1 to 2 teaspoon sugar.
"Ice" cake with mayonnaise, completely sealing.
Refrigerate overnight or 8 hours. Toss before serving.
Keeps several days in fridge.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Combine vegetables; drain.
Add sugar, vinegar and spices; heat to a boil.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Put relish in hot jars and seal.
Makes approximately 7 pints.
This relish goes exceptionally well with white or brown gravy.

title: hershey's best brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In medium microwave-safe bowl heat butter on High until melted.
Stir in sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add cocoa and beat until well blended.
Add flour, baking powder and salt; beat well.
Pour into pan; bake 30 to 35 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan. Cool and cut.

title: mexican dip
directions: Cook hamburger and sausage together.
Drain grease.
Pour sausage and hamburger into a crock-pot.
Add cheeses, chopped up. Pour in picante sauce.
Allow for cheeses to melt.
Serve hot with chips.
Great appetizer!

title: mediterranean pilaf(servings:  8)
directions: Bring to boil in 1-quart saucepan.
Pour chicken broth into mixture.
Cook covered over low heat 20 minutes or until all liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.
Turmeric and curry powder add brilliant golden color and delicate flavor.
Serving Ideas:
Goes great with beef kabobs, chicken, etc.

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in the water; let congeal for a few minutes (not too long).
Let cream cheese get room temperature.
Mix with mixer or hand.
Cream the cream cheese.
Add mayonnaise and crushed pineapple.
Mix well.
Add milk, then add jello to mixture and let congeal.

title: cinnamon-raisin muffins
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour, cereal, 1/4 cup sugar, baking powder and cinnamon; set aside.

title: creamy hot dog casserole
directions: Pare and cut potatoes.
Cook potatoes and beans until almost done.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour and stir.
Add milk; heat to boiling.
Boil mixture until it thickens.
Remove from heat and add onions and mayonnaise.
Stir to blend.
Slice hot dogs into chunks.
Layer hot dogs, potatoes and beans in casserole.
Top with sauce.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together until fluffy. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each. Add flavoring and coconut. Mix well. Sift together flour, baking power and salt three times. Add alternately with milk. Put into a tube pan that has been greased with shortening and floured. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300° and ice with icing.

title: trilby parfait(recipe of past president, mrs. meredith j. cox)
directions: Whip the cream; add sugar and chill, then add the prepared fruit, nuts and chocolate creams.
Pack in freezer surrounded by ice and salt and let stand for 2 hours before serving.

title: diabetic loaf
directions: Mix all together and cook in loaf pan.

title: caramel cashew bars
directions: Press 4 rolls together and roll into a 9 x 13-inch rectangle pan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Sprinkle with 1 1/2 cups chocolate chips. Repeat with remaining rolls and place over top of the chocolate chips. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Let cool.

title: one dish meal
directions: Brown meat well.
Add onions, bay leaf, soup and water.
Mix well.
Add carrots and cook about 45 minutes.
When almost done, add potatoes.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and bell pepper.
Add garlic salt when done.
Add all sauces and let simmer.
Cook noodles until soft, then place in casserole dish.
Pour sauce, then place more noodles.
Repeat.
Put cheese on top and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted good.

title: chicken dinners in foil(method:  foil)
directions: Divide the rice in 4 equal parts.
Place part on a sheet of heavy-duty foil; sprinkle with 1 tablespoon soup mix.
Arrange the chicken on the rice, then pour 2 tablespoons milk on each serving of chicken.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon soup mix; place 1 teaspoon butter on top.
Fold the foil, sealing tightly.
Place on a grill over hot coals; cook for 1 hour, or until chicken is done.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and blend well. Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 3 3/4 cups mix (about fifteen 6 ounce servings).

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Boil until soft.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool, then cut into squares.

title: chocolate chip-nut brownies
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients together.
Beat egg yolks with 1 tablespoon water.
Add to mixture.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle nuts and chocolate chips over top.
Beat egg whites with 1 1/4 cups brown sugar.
Put over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: black-eyed peas
directions: Brown sausage, drain.
Add vegetables to pan (green pepper, onions and garlic).
Cook until tender.
Mix with sausage.
Add peas with liquid, tomato sauce, pepper and oregano.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Cook chicken.
Remove from bone and cut in pieces.
Toast bread and tear in pieces.
Combine broth and celery soup and heat together.
Pour over chicken and toasted bread (which have been combined).
Add salt and pepper to taste and mix well.
Cook until heated through in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish in a 375° oven.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Grease cookie sheet. Sift together the flour, soda, cinnamon, ginger and salt.
Put into large bowl the shortening, sugar, egg and molasses. Beat about 1 minute.
Add the sour milk or buttermilk and raisins.
Add sifted flour mixture. Beat until blended, 1 minute. Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° about 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: coconut colada
directions: Pour all ingredients into blender.
Blend on high speed until smooth.
Pour into glass.
May be garnished with fruit.

title: cherry pie salad
directions: Fold all ingredients together.
Chill until firm.

title: family favorite meat loaf
directions: Combine eggs with milk, bread crumbs, onion, salt, sage and meat.
Mix well and shape into 9 x 5-inch rectangle or oval, or about 6-inch round.
Carefully place in slow cooking pot.
Cook on low for five to six hours.
Combine sauce ingredients in small bowl; pour over meat.
Cover and cook on high 15 minutes longer. Slice and serve while hot or use cold slices for sandwiches.

title: roasted asparagus
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees.

title: strawberry pound cake
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together.
Pour in a floured and greased tube pan.
Bake at about 325° for 1 hour.

title: grandma's hot dish
directions: In large iron skillet, brown meat and onion.
Add salt, pepper and garlic salt.
When onion is transparent and meat is brown, add 2 cans Veg-All.
Let simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and place biscuits on top.
Place in oven.
Bake at 400° until biscuits are brown.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tess' rice pudding
directions: Heat milk and rice to boiling point.
Cover and lower heat. Simmer 35 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: potato skillet dinner
directions: Brown the meat with the onion; drain fat.
Add the water, parsley, potatoes and spices; bring to a boil.
Turn down to a simmer and cover, stirring frequently, to keep the potatoes from sticking.
(Add more water, if necessary.) Cook for 10 to 15 minutes, or until potatoes just begin to get tender.
Stir in peas; cook another 6 to 8 minutes, still covered, stirring occasionally to keep from sticking.
(Leftovers make great burritos.)
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake for 10 minutes at 450°.
Top with 1 cup grated Cheddar cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Pour warm beer over mixture and stir well.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan and bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and butter the top well and return to oven for 30 minutes more.

title: cheese fondue casserole(good for brunch)
directions: The night before:
Butter bread and place in a buttered baking pan.
Sprinkle part of cheese on top.
Beat eggs well.
Add milk and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over bread and cheese.
Cover and allow to stand in refrigerator overnight.
Allow to come to room temperature the next day.
Place in a 350° oven for 1 hour (or more).
Fondue is done when a knife is inserted and comes out clean.
Serves 8.

title: yum yum cabbage
directions: Saute ground beef, chopped pepper and chopped onion.
Add rice.
In baking dish, add 1/2 of meat and rice mixture.
Next, layer 1/2 of cabbage, then layer 1 can of soup undiluted.
Repeat with balance of meat/rice mixture, cabbage and soup.
Blend last 4 ingredients, making a sweet and sour sauce.
Spread over top. Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix soups, onion and chili powder together.
Grease bottom of casserole dish, lay tortilla chips on bottom, chicken next, soups next, pour Ro-Tel over this and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Serve with chips.

title: small cherry cream cheese cakes
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing thoroughly.
Add vanilla.
Fill small muffin tins 3/4 full of batter.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Put 1 teaspoon cherry topping on each.
Return to oven and bake 5 minutes more.
Cool, then refrigerate.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: In a large bowl, layer the ingredients one on top of another. (Spread the mayonnaise as if "frosting" the salad.)
Sprinkle the cheese, then bacon, then the sugar on top.
Cover.
Put in fridge overnight (8 hours).
Toss just before serving.

title: chicken saute gabelou
directions: Salt, pepper and brown chicken in 1/4 cup butter.
Remove chicken from skillet, add mushrooms to remaining fat, cook for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Return chicken to skillet, add bourbon, broth and tomato paste, also Worcestershire.
Cover and bring to boil.
Simmer 20 minutes or until tender.
Transfer chicken to serving dish.
Blend flour and 1 tablespoon butter until smooth.
Add to sauce.
Cook and stir until thick.
Add pimento, pour over chicken.
Serves 4.

title: beef and noodle casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Boil egg noodles according to package instructions.
Drain and rinse with cold water after cooked.
Cut onions.
Heat skillet; add oil.
Brown onions, then add meat. Drain excess oil after cooked.
Add cooked noodles, tomato soup and green beans to meat mixture.
Mix well.
Garnish top with grated cheese.
Bake for approximately 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbles and cheese melts.

title: favorite broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, cauliflower, bacon, onion, tomatoes and eggs. Combine mayonnaise, sugar, salt and vinegar. Mix well. Pour over vegetables and toss. Serves 6 to 8.

title: charlie parker special
directions: Stir ingredients together well.
Add a large piece of ice. Later as the ice melts, add a pint of liquor and 1/2 gallon of wine and more ginger ale.

title: chicken breasts with shredded mushrooms
directions: In a small saucepan bring broth to a boil.
Cook until reduced to 1 cup (about 5 minutes).
Set aside.
Combine flour, pepper and salt, sprinkle over chicken, both sides.
Coat a large skillet with cooking spray, place over medium heat until hot.
Add chicken, cook 5 minutes per side or until browned.
Remove chicken from skillet and set aside.
Add butter to skillet, heat until melts, then add mushrooms and shallots, stirring constantly. Saute until tender.
Combine 1 Tbsp. sherry and cornstarch, stir well, set aside.
Add remaining 3 Tbsp sherry and broth to skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Cook until sauce is reduced to 3/4 cup.
Add cornstarch mixture.
Cook stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened.
Return chicken to skillet, cover, reduce heat and simmer for about 10 minutes.
Transfer chicken to a serving plate, top evenly with mushroom mixture.
Sprinkle with freshly cut parsley.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup and sour cream. Combine with chicken. Top with cracker crumbs and butter.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: apple bread
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees. Grease and flour loaf pan. Mix 1 c. sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla. Stir in flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt until smooth. Stir in apples and nuts. spread in pan. Mix 1 Tbsp. sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over batter. Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean; It takes about 50-60 minutes. Immediately remove from pan; cool bread completely before slicing. Store tightly covered.

title: cheese filled jumbo shells
directions: Cook jumbo shells according to package directions; drain. Cool in a single layer on wax paper or aluminum foil to keep shells from sticking together.

title: pete's pumpkin pie
directions: Roll out pastry and line a 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Cool shell.
Combine pumpkin, sugar and spices.
Beat in eggs and cream.
If desired, stir in rum.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and sour cream well.
Pour 1/2 of the batter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over cake batter.
Pour remaining batter in pan.
Swirl with knife.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Mix powdered sugar, milk and vanilla.
Pour over cake while hot.

title: preacher roscoe's pizza
directions: Grease two 14-inch pizza pans.
Spread dough out thin on pans. Add sauce and ground beef.
Sprinkle cheese lightly over this.
Add pepperoni.
Top with rest of cheese.
Bake at 425° for 17 minutes.

title: cabbage and beef soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown beef.
Add all remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 1 hour, covered.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: peanut butter maple cookies
directions: Cream the butter, peanut butter and brown sugar together. Beat in maple syrup, egg and vanilla.
Add flour with baking soda to liquid ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls 3 inches apart and flatten with a fork that has been dipped in flour.
Bake in a 375° oven for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in layer dish at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: dirty rice
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Add all ingredients and simmer.
Add 1 cup of uncooked rice.
Simmer until rice is tender. Remove bay leaves and serve hot.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into greased 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: puffs for filling
directions: Heat margarine, salt and water to boiling.
Add flour.
Stir over medium heat until mixture forms a soft ball and leaves sides of pan.
Let cool to room temperature.
Place dough in mixing bowl.
Add eggs one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased baking sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Fill with your favorite chicken salad, ham salad or cream filling.

title: ramos gin fizz
directions: *Use empty lemonade can.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix all together, except whipped cream.
Add whipped cream and freeze overnight.

title: carolina low country she-crab soup
directions: Forty five minutes before serving, combine milk, mace and lemon peel in top of double boiler.
Let simmer over direct heat for 7 minutes.
Add crabmeat, butter and creams. Heat over boiling water for 15 minutes.
Remove lemon peel; add crumbs and season. Let stand over low heat for 3 minutes.
Just before serving, add sherry and hard-cooked egg yolks in bottom of each soup plate. Add soup.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: orange salad
directions: Heat juice to boiling point.
Add jello and sugar while hot. Dissolve thoroughly.
Add pineapple and sour cream.
Mix well.

title: spinach squares
directions: Drain spinach very well.
Mix spinach, Mozzarella, pepperoni, oil, garlic powder and Parmesan.
In another bowl mix flour, milk and eggs with electric mixer.
Add to spinach mixture and blend well.
Pour into 13X9 pan and bake at 350 degrees for 30-45 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.
Let stand; cream oleo, eggs and sugar.
Stir in other ingredients.
Bake at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 minutes.
Top with favorite frosting.

title: sunday school brownies
directions: Melt margarine. Stir in cocoa and sugar. Add beaten eggs. Add flour; mix well. Spread in greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: caramel pecan dream bars
directions: Beat together.
Press in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: mike's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together butter flavor Crisco, brown sugar, white sugar, eggs and vanilla. Sift and stir into Crisco combo: flour, baking soda, salt and chocolate chips. Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheets. Bake at 375 degrees for 8 to minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix in a bowl.

title: broiled pork chops
directions: Arrange pork chops on broiler pan.
Sprinkle with dry onion soup mix.
Broil in oven until done.

title: broccoli salad and dressing
directions: Mix mayonnaise, onion, sugar and vinegar together and pour over broccoli flowerets.
Toss and add bacon bits.

title: marinated mixed vegetables
directions: Cut all vegetables into bite-size pieces (leave mushrooms whole, choose small ones).
Blend remaining ingredients for marinade in a large container with cover.
Add vegetables and refrigerate overnight, stirring gently occasionally.
Keeps quite a while in the refrigerator, although the mushrooms will darken. Adapted from Ortho Pickle Book.

title: angel hair and shrimp
directions: Prepare angel hair according to directions and drain.

In a large skillet, heat olive oil and butter. Add shrimp and garlic. Cook and stir until shrimp are opaque. Combine hot angel hair, shrimp mixture, Parmesan cheese, dill, salt and pepper. Toss to mix.
Arrange on warm serving platter and serve immediately. Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: baked beans with hamburger
directions: Saute bacon and onion in pan.
Add beef and brown.
Add the rest of ingredients and mix.
Pour in covered baking dish and bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: danish puffs
directions: Cut 1/2 cup oleo into 1 cup of flour until it resembles coarse meal.
Add cold water and stir until well blended.
Divide dough in half.
Press each half into a 12 x 3-inch oblong on an ungreased baking sheet.
Place boiling water and remaining 1/2 cup of oleo into saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add almond extract and remove from heat.
Stir in remaining 1 cup of flour.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Spread this mixture over the oblongs.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for about 50 minutes.

title: swiss chicken cutlets
directions: Cut each cheese slice in half.
Place 1/2 on top of each cutlet.
Starting with a short end, tightly roll up cutlets jelly roll style.
Tie securely with string.
On waxed paper, combine flour and pepper; mix well.
Add cutlets; toss gently to coat.

title: chow mein
directions: In large skillet, cook pork in 1 tablespoon hot salad oil until done, about 10 minutes.
Remove from skillet.
Cook celery, onions and mushrooms in 2 tablespoons salad oil until crisp-tender, 2 to 3 minutes, stirring often.

title: garlic-buttered green beans
directions: Cook green beans until tender.
In a skillet, saute mushrooms in butter until tender.
Add onion and garlic powders.
Drain beans; add to skillet and toss.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: italian hamburger bake
directions: Cook meat and onion together until brown.
Drain well.
Stir in soup mix, milk and cottage cheese.
Add spices.
Put in casserole dish and sprinkle with cheese.
Place biscuits on top and bake until biscuits are brown.

title: ham and cheese roll-ups
directions: Separate crescent rolls into triangles; slice triangles in half to form two smaller triangles.
Slice cheese and ham on crescent dough.
Roll from wide end.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake for 13 minutes at 350°.
Makes 32.
Serve with French's sweet mustard for dipping.

title: bread pudding
directions: Toast bread and spread with butter while hot.
Arrange toast in a buttered baking pan.
Sprinkle with raisins.
Stir salt and all but 2 tablespoons of the sugar into the eggs and mix well. Pour over the toast and let stand 10 minutes to soak bread.

title: country chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients, eggs, oil and milk, stirring constantly. When it becomes thick, remove from heat.
Add vanilla and butter. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° for about 30 minutes. Be sure to watch closely so that crust doesn't brown too fast (you may need to adjust heat).

title: pie crust
directions: Mix, then roll out on pastry cloth.
Then bake.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Saute onions in butter until soft.
Combine eggs and sour cream.
Add to onion mixture.
Add seasonings.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake on lowest rack, 20 minutes at 450° and then 15 minutes at 325°.

title: spackle prints
directions: Mix water and spackling powder to the consistency of whipped cream.
Be sure mixture is free of lumps.
Add colored powdered paint and pour into container.
Spackle may be dropped on waxed paper and then collage materials embedded in it.
Spackle is superior to Plaster of Paris because it dries more slowly, allowing children time to change their minds about designs.
The finished product takes 40 minutes to 1 hour to dry.

title: beef or chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix beef or chicken, olives, 2 tablespoons onion and 1 cup Cheddar.
Brush tortillas on both sides with melted butter.
Fill with mixture and roll up.
Place in buttered baking dish. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese, 1 tablespoon onion and pour sauce over all.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: banana berry dessert
directions: Prepare pudding with milk as directed. Fold in sour cream and set aside.
Line bottom of a 3-quart clear glass bowl with vanilla wafers.
Slice one banana on top; arrange. Top with 1/3 of strawberries, then 1/3 of blueberries. Spoon 1/3 of pudding over fruit. Repeat the layers twice more, ending with pudding.
Top with Cool Whip. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.

title: dutch potatoes
directions: Peel the potatoes and remove the centers with an apple corer. Drag a frankfurter and wiener through each potato and place in baking pan with the drippings.
Add the milk and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Yields 6 servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain
vegetables
and layer in a casserole.
Saute the onion in butter until tender.
Add drained mushrooms and cream of chicken
soup.
Mix
until a liquid.
Add salt and pepper. Pour over
the
vegetables
in
the casserole.
Top with your favorite grated cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: easy taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet and drain.

Add taco seasoning and water according to package directions and simmer 10 minutes. Spread beef in shallow dish and top with shredded Cheddar cheese. Top with chopped lettuce and tomatoes and sprinkle on taco sauce. Serve with nacho chips and sour cream.
Makes a great snack for guests and is perfect for lunch or a light supper.

title: cranberry congealed salad
directions: Add hot water to Jell-O and cranberry sauce. Mix well. Add nuts, pineapple and celery. Refrigerate until congealed.

title: ice cream torte
directions: Mix first five ingredients together.
Pat on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until light brown.
Cool and break up in pieces.
Put 1/2 in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 12 ounce jar of caramel topping over pieces.
Put 1/2 gallon ice cream on top. Sprinkle with other 1/2 of crumbs and freeze.

title: creole franks
directions: Brown wieners, onion and pepper in skillet with margarine on medium-high heat.
Add tomatoes, soup and seasonings.
Cover and bring to steaming on high.
Turn to low for 15 minutes.
(Serve over steamed rice or in a ring of mashed potatoes.)

title: tamale casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Preheat oven to 350°. Chop and spread tamales evenly in dish.
Drain and layer can of corn.
Pour off top liquid of beans, but use the good juice. Layer on top of corn.
Spread chili on bean layer.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350°
for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spicy vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Add onion and garlic. Add remaining ingredients and simmer. Wonderful!!

title: apple kuchen
directions: Blend
together cake mix, coconut and margarine;
press mixture in	bottom	and up sides of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread apple
pie filling over the first layer.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together;
sprinkle
over
pie filling.
Blend sour cream and
1 beaten
egg
together; spoon evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix together the rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: best ever pie crust
directions: Mix until forms ball.
Chill in refrigerator before rolling out.
Makes enough for 2 pies.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine
lard,
sugar
and
1/2 cups hot water.
Dissolve the yeast in
cup warm water.
Add eggs and salt.
Mix, then add yeast mixture.
Work in flour.
Dough will be sticky.
Let rise until double. Work out and let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add all ingredients except the biscuits.
Heat until boiling.
Remove from heat.
Add biscuits and stir.
Pour mixture into a greased tube pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: pineapple jello slices
directions: Make Jell-O using 1 cup hot water.
Add this to the drained pineapple slices in the can (you will have some Jell-O left over). Place can in refrigerator overnight.
To unmold, remove bottom of can, loosen sides with a knife and push out.
Cut into slices. Red and green make a pretty plate at Christmas.

title: wild rice and chicken soup
directions: Saute onion in butter. Add flour to make a thick roux. Slowly add broth and half and half using a whisk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened. Add rice, salt, chicken, vegetables and parsley. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes. If soup is too thick, thin with extra broth.

title: cheeseburger rice
directions: *Or use 1 cup (4 ounces) Kraft natural shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: peanut taffy
directions: Put sugar and water in saucepan and boil until the sugar is dissolved and becomes dark and clear.
Add butter.
Stir until butter melts, then boil for 15 minutes or until syrup reaches hard crack stage (325°).
Add peanuts.
Stir and remove from heat. Spread candy on buttered baking sheets or press into buttered patty pans.
Cut or break into irregular pieces.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Blend all ingredients, except pecans, in 2-quart microwavable dish.
Heat in microwave 3 to 5 minutes (depends on wattage of your oven).
After heating, stir ingredients until smooth.
Mix in pecans.
Pour into an 8-inch dish.
Refrigerate until fudge is firm.

title: chocolate eagle brand cookies
directions: Melt together milk, chocolate chips and butter.
Bring to a boil and cook for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in flour and nuts.
Drop by spoon on cookie sheet with foil.
Bake at 325° for 8 minutes.

title: sausage n' gravy
directions: Crumble sausage into large heavy frypan.
Cook over medium-low heat.
Add onion and cook until sausage becomes brown.
Discard all but 3 tablespoons of drippings.
Stir in flour.
Cook over medium-low heat.
Stir in milk and add seasoning.
Cook, stirring, until thickened.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except juice.
Spoon into deep pie plate.
Pour juice over top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and cook over low heat for 1 minute.
Mix the paprika, chili powder, cumin and vinegar juice, then add the remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Fry beef
until
brown.
Drain.
Add
tomato
sauce and spices and set
aside.
On
greased
pizza
pan, lay crescents (reserving 4 for the center) around the pan, leaving about 1/4 of each crescent extending	out
over
the	edge of the pan in spoke fashion.
Fit
the	4 reserved rolls in center, pinching dough and fitting
rolls
together.	Spoon
beef mixture into center and sprinkle
cheese
over
to	cover.	Bring extended crescent points up over meat and cheese, pressing and pinching dough to hold mixture
in.
Brush
top
lightly with milk and sprinkle sesame seed
over top, completely covering.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes until browned.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting in pie wedges.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Melt chocolate in a large Tupperware bowl 2 minutes on High in microwave.
Add milk and butter to melted chocolate.
Stir well. Add nuts and stir. Add marshmallows and stir. Spread mixture in oblong pan or Pyrex dish, well-greased. Refrigerate until hard. Cut into squares.
Takes 10 minutes to make. Freezes well.
Easy for children to make.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Coat a large Dutch oven with cooking spray.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into Dutch oven.
Bring to boil. Cover, reduce heat, simmer 20 minutes or until crisp-tender, stirring occasionally.

title: cheesy cheesy macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Over low heat, heat up evaporated milk until almost a boil.
Add cheese.
Stir constantly until all cheese is melted.
Add pepper.
Drain macaroni and put into casserole dish; stir in cheese sauce and mix well.
Additional shredded cheese may be scattered over top of mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: dreamsicle pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into a graham cracker crust.
Chill.
Decorate with mandarin orange slices.

title: ricotta gnocchi
directions: Mix all together.
Knead until it comes away from bowl side. Divide dough into 4 balls.
Roll out and make pencil thin.
Cut into 3/4-inch.
Press middle to curl.
Cook for 10 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken, vegetables, salt and pepper together.
Place in baking dish.
Mix Bisquick with enough milk to pour over ingredients in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until golden brown.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Place chicken in frying pan with olive oil, chopped parsley, celery, garlic, salt and pepper.
Brown thoroughly on all sides over moderate flame.
When chicken is well browned, add bay leaves and after 1 minute, add the wine.
Cook gently until wine is almost evaporated.
Add water.
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes, until chicken is done.

title: lemon-dijon chicken breasts
directions: Combine bread crumbs and lemon rind in a zip-top plastic bag, shaking well to mix.

title: chili and rice
directions: Crumble ground chuck in 2-quart casserole dish.
Add chopped onions.
Microwave on High 4 to 6 minutes; stir halfway through cooking.
Drain.
Dissolve Chili-O mix in 1/2 cup water.
Add this along with the tomatoes and beans to the cooked ground chuck and onions.
Microwave, loosely covered, on High 8 to 10 minutes. Stir halfway through cooking.
Simmer on 50% power for an additional 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Slice cookie dough with knife ideal for cutting sticky stuff. Heat oven to 350°.
Cut off ends of package and cut wrapper along the seam.
Remove dough from wrapper.
Slice well-chilled dough into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Place them 2 inches apart on ungreased, ovenproof cookie pan.
Sprinkle with sugar, if desired. Bake at 350° for 7 to 11 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove and let them cool for 1 minute.

title: meta's pound cake
directions: Thoroughly cream butter and sugar.
Add extracts.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
On low speed, stir in the sifted flour and soda mixture.
Add sour cream and stir to combine.
Using a tube pan or three loaf pans, cut wax paper to fit the bottom of pan or pans.
Spray pans well with cooking oil and line with paper.

Place the cake in the middle of the oven with a pan of hot water on the bottom rack of oven, which should be heated to 300°. Bake until cake tests done, about 1 1/2 hours or a little longer, about 1 hour and 15 minutes for loaf pans.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Sift flour and sugar.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Work into ball and knead 10 minutes.
Pat dough into 2 1/4-inch thick 14 x 12-inch rectangle, on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cut into 2-inch diamonds or squares with sharp knife.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes. Re-cut cookies and separate very carefully.
Remove from baking sheet.
Handle carefully.
Store with paper between layers in airtight container.
Lasts well for weeks.

title: quick quiche
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch pie pan.
Mix Bisquick, milk/cheese, eggs and oleo in blender for 2 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour half of the mixture into pie pan. Add 2 tablespoons bacon bits and 1 scallion, cut into small pieces. Pour in remaining mixture. Sprinkle with parsley flakes and paprika.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Heat eggs; add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Add flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nuts.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: hard pretzel snacks
directions: Marinate pretzel pieces in all ingredients at least 4 hours. Stir often.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cranberry, pears and apples
directions: Boil sugar and water for 3 minutes; add cranberries and boil for 2 more minutes.
Add apples and pears to mixture and boil another 8 minutes.
Delicious!
Put in a pretty bowl.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix margarine, eggs and sugar together well.
Add rest of ingredients and the blueberries last.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes, possibly 30 to 35 minutes.

title: marvelous marble cheesecake(microwave)
directions: Melt margarine, then combine sugar and crumbs.
Press firmly against bottom and sides.
Cook 1 minute on Full power or until bubbling near edges.
Beat the cream cheese until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat in sugar and vanilla until smooth and creamy.
Pour over crust.

title: world's best pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350° 10 minutes before Sally Lunn is ready to be baked.
Grease a 10-inch tube cake pan or a Bundt pan.
Heat the milk, shortening and 1/4 cup water until very warm, about 120°.
Shortening does not need to melt.
Blend 1 1/3 cups flour, the sugar, salt and dry yeast in a large mixing bowl.
Blend warm liquids into flour mixture.
Beat with an electric mixer at medium speed about 2 minutes, scraping the sides of the bowl occasionally (use regular beaters).

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done, then remove skin and bones and divide into small pieces.
Mix with remaining ingredients and bake, covered, for 1 hour at 325°.
Serve over rice.

title: graham cracker fruit cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients except oleo and marshmallows. Melt these together and pour into mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and chill.
Keep refrigerated.
This will keep a long time in the refrigerator.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour four 1 pound coffee cans.
Fill half full and bake 1 hour at 325°.
Bake at least 1 day before serving.
Slice and garnish with whipped cream and a cherry.

title: hamburger skillet dinner
directions: Cut up bacon and fry until crisp.
Add hamburger and chopped onions; brown.
Add soy sauce, pepper and water.
Add the vegetables in layers:
potatoes, green pepper, tomatoes, celery and cabbage.
